WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:45.225 --> 00:01:48.061
Three of a kind. let's do this.
That's it? Three guys?

3
00:01:48.228 --> 00:01:51.565
Two guys on the roof. Every
guy gets a share. Five shares is plenty.

4
00:01:51.732 --> 00:01:54.192
Six shares. Don't
forget the guy who planned the job.

5
00:01:54.359 --> 00:01:56.653
He thinks he can sit it out
and still take a slice.

6
00:01:56.820 --> 00:01:59.948
- I know why they call him the Joker.
Why do they call him the Joker?

7
00:02:00.115 --> 00:02:01.950
I heard he wears makeup.
Makeup?

8
00:02:02.117 --> 00:02:04.077
Yeah. to scare people.
You know. war paint.

9
00:02:16.632 --> 00:02:19.843
All right. everybody.
hands up. heads down!

10
00:02:20.219 --> 00:02:23.013
I said. hands up. heads down!

11
00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:26.141
Let's go. pal.
I'm making a withdrawal here.

12
00:02:26.391 --> 00:02:27.851
- I said. hands up!
- No!

13
00:02:28.227 --> 00:02:30.479
Here comes the silent alarm.

14
00:02:30.646 --> 00:02:31.980
And there it goes.

15
00:02:32.147 --> 00:02:33.357
Heads down!

16
00:02:33.524 --> 00:02:35.859
All right. tootsie.
you're taking a dive with me.

17
00:02:36.026 --> 00:02:38.695
- Down! I said. stay down there!
Don't hurt me!

18
00:02:38.946 --> 00:02:41.949
Funny. it didn't dial 911.
It was trying to reach a private number.

19
00:02:42.115 --> 00:02:44.034
Is it a problem?
No. I'm done here.

20
00:02:53.418 --> 00:02:55.796
Sit down! Down!

21
00:02:56.296 --> 00:02:58.465
Down! I said. stay down there!

22
00:03:02.719 --> 00:03:05.556
Obviously we don't want you
doing anything with your hands...

23
00:03:05.722 --> 00:03:08.642
...other than holding on for dear life.

24
00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:18.402
On the ground! Stay on the ground!

25
00:03:18.569 --> 00:03:22.239
Nobody make a move!
Nobody! Stay down!

26
00:03:38.672 --> 00:03:39.715
Yeah!

27
00:03:42.551 --> 00:03:44.636
You have any idea
who you're stealing from?

28
00:03:44.803 --> 00:03:48.515
- You and your friends are dead.
He's out. right?

29
00:03:51.602 --> 00:03:52.853
What...?

30
00:04:00.694 --> 00:04:02.446
Where did you learn to count?

31
00:04:05.240 --> 00:04:07.284
They wired this thing up
with like 5000 volts.

32
00:04:07.451 --> 00:04:08.702
What kind of bank does that?

33
00:04:08.869 --> 00:04:11.914
A Mob bank.
I guess the Joker's as crazy as they say.

34
00:04:12.080 --> 00:04:13.123
Where's the alarm guy?

35
00:04:13.290 --> 00:04:15.792
Boss told me when the guy
was done. I should take him out.

36
00:04:15.959 --> 00:04:17.294
One less share. right?

37
00:04:18.212 --> 00:04:20.464
Funny. he told me something similar.

38
00:04:20.631 --> 00:04:22.090
He what? No! No!

39
00:04:33.810 --> 00:04:35.187
That's a lot of money.

40
00:04:35.354 --> 00:04:39.066
If this Joker guy was so smart.
he'd have had us bring a bigger car.

41
00:04:40.484 --> 00:04:44.404
I'm betting the Joker told you to kill me
soon as we loaded the cash.

42
00:04:45.322 --> 00:04:49.117
No. no. no. I kill the bus driver.

43
00:04:49.826 --> 00:04:50.953
Bus driver?

44
00:04:53.163 --> 00:04:54.665
What bus driver?

45
00:04:58.752 --> 00:05:00.671
School's out. Time to go.

46
00:05:00.837 --> 00:05:03.090
That guy's not getting up. is he?

47
00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.509
That's a lot of money.

48
00:05:09.012 --> 00:05:11.348
What happened to the rest of the guys?

49
00:05:18.105 --> 00:05:20.482
You think you're smart. huh?

50
00:05:21.191 --> 00:05:22.818
The guy that hired youse...

51
00:05:23.360 --> 00:05:25.946
...he'll just do the same to you.

52
00:05:26.238 --> 00:05:29.199
Oh. criminals in this town
used to believe in things.

53
00:05:29.366 --> 00:05:30.659
Honor...

54
00:05:30.826 --> 00:05:32.536
...respect.

55
00:05:32.703 --> 00:05:35.038
Look at you.
What do you believe in. huh?

56
00:05:35.205 --> 00:05:36.498
What do you believe in?!

57
00:05:36.832 --> 00:05:41.753
I believe whatever doesn't kill you
simply makes you...

58
00:05:43.338 --> 00:05:44.882
...stranger.

59
00:06:26.840 --> 00:06:29.760
Mr. Mayor. you were elected
in a campaign to clean up the city.

60
00:06:29.927 --> 00:06:32.095
- When are you gonna start?
I already have.

61
00:06:32.262 --> 00:06:33.347
Like this Batman.

62
00:06:33.513 --> 00:06:36.099
We're hearing he's doing good.
criminals are running scared.

63
00:06:36.266 --> 00:06:39.978
- No. man. I don't like it tonight.
- What are you. superstitious?

64
00:06:40.145 --> 00:06:43.232
You got more chance of winning
the Powerball than running into him.

65
00:06:43.398 --> 00:06:46.777
That's not true. Our men in the
Major Crimes Unit are close to an arrest.

66
00:06:46.944 --> 00:06:49.905
Hey. Wuertz. mayor says
you're closing in on the Batman.

67
00:06:50.072 --> 00:06:52.199
The investigation is ongoing.

68
00:06:52.366 --> 00:06:54.785
The process of cleaning up
the streets is a long one.

69
00:06:54.952 --> 00:06:56.954
I pledged in my campaign. uh. to have...

70
00:07:01.291 --> 00:07:03.585
Ever intending to see your wife again.
lieutenant?

71
00:07:03.752 --> 00:07:06.421
I thought you had to
go look after your mother. detective.

72
00:07:06.588 --> 00:07:08.549
Checked her back into the hospital.

73
00:07:09.007 --> 00:07:10.634
I'm sorry.

74
00:07:11.134 --> 00:07:14.429
- So he hasn't shown up?
- He often doesn't.

75
00:07:14.805 --> 00:07:16.515
I like reminding everybody
he's out there.

76
00:07:16.682 --> 00:07:17.975
Why wouldn't he come?

77
00:07:18.308 --> 00:07:20.143
Hopefully...

78
00:07:20.644 --> 00:07:22.187
...because he's busy.

79
00:07:38.912 --> 00:07:41.832
That's why we bring dogs.

80
00:07:41.999 --> 00:07:44.334
- My little princes.
Please.

81
00:07:44.501 --> 00:07:48.088
Please. they're crawling in my mouth.
Please. I beg you. get them off.

82
00:07:48.255 --> 00:07:51.008
Look what your drugs
do to my customers.

83
00:07:51.174 --> 00:07:52.801
Buyer beware.

84
00:07:52.968 --> 00:07:56.179
I told you my compound
would take you places.

85
00:07:56.346 --> 00:07:59.099
I never said they'd be places
you wanted to go.

86
00:07:59.266 --> 00:08:01.810
My business. repeat customers.

87
00:08:01.977 --> 00:08:03.687
You don't like
what I have to offer...

88
00:08:03.854 --> 00:08:05.606
...you can buy from someone else.

89
00:08:05.772 --> 00:08:08.525
Assuming Batman left anyone
to buy from.

90
00:08:11.862 --> 00:08:15.866
My dogs are hungry.

91
00:08:19.494 --> 00:08:21.872
Pity there's only one of you.

92
00:08:29.838 --> 00:08:31.506
What...?
That's not him.

93
00:08:35.886 --> 00:08:37.638
Loose the dogs!

94
00:08:50.359 --> 00:08:51.902
That's more like it.

95
00:10:19.990 --> 00:10:21.742
Don't let me find you out here again.

96
00:10:21.909 --> 00:10:24.745
- We're trying to help you.
I don't need help.

97
00:10:24.912 --> 00:10:26.246
Not my diagnosis.

98
00:10:26.413 --> 00:10:30.000
What gives you the right? What's
the difference between you and me?

99
00:10:30.167 --> 00:10:33.045
I'm not wearing hockey pads.

100
00:10:36.548 --> 00:10:38.508
Everybody back now!

101
00:10:40.677 --> 00:10:43.847
He can't resist showing us his face.

102
00:10:48.101 --> 00:10:50.270
What's he hiding under that makeup?

103
00:10:57.986 --> 00:11:00.656
Uh. can we get a minute.
people. please?

104
00:11:03.283 --> 00:11:05.452
Him again. Who are the others?

105
00:11:05.619 --> 00:11:07.204
Another bunch of smalltimers.

106
00:11:08.580 --> 00:11:10.290
Some of the marked bills I gave you.

107
00:11:10.457 --> 00:11:12.751
My detectives have been
making drug buys with them.

108
00:11:12.918 --> 00:11:15.504
This bank was another drop for the Mob.
That makes five.

109
00:11:15.671 --> 00:11:18.257
- We found the bulk of their dirty cash.
- Time to move in.

110
00:11:18.423 --> 00:11:22.219
We'd have to hit all banks
simultaneously. SWAT teams. backup.

111
00:11:22.553 --> 00:11:24.221
What about this Joker guy?

112
00:11:24.388 --> 00:11:27.349
One man or the entire Mob? He can wait.

113
00:11:27.516 --> 00:11:29.851
When the new DA hears about this.
he'll want in.

114
00:11:30.018 --> 00:11:32.563
- Do you trust him?
- Be hard to keep him out.

115
00:11:32.729 --> 00:11:36.191
I hear he's as stubborn as you are.

116
00:12:19.735 --> 00:12:22.696
Be nice when Wayne Manor's rebuilt.

117
00:12:22.863 --> 00:12:25.574
You can swap
not sleeping in a penthouse...

118
00:12:25.741 --> 00:12:27.284
...for not sleeping in a mansion.

119
00:12:27.451 --> 00:12:31.205
Whenever you stitch yourself up.
you do make a bloody mess.

120
00:12:31.371 --> 00:12:34.374
Yeah. It makes me learn
from my mistakes.

121
00:12:34.541 --> 00:12:37.961
You ought to be pretty knowledgeable
by now. then.

122
00:12:39.671 --> 00:12:40.714
My armor.

123
00:12:40.881 --> 00:12:44.468
I'm carrying too much weight.
I need to be... I need to be faster.

124
00:12:44.635 --> 00:12:47.304
I'm sure Mr. Fox can oblige.

125
00:12:47.471 --> 00:12:49.973
- Did you get mauled by a tiger?
- It was a dog.

126
00:12:50.140 --> 00:12:52.684
- Huh?
- It was a big dog.

127
00:12:52.851 --> 00:12:56.730
There were more copycats last night.
Alfred. with guns.

128
00:12:56.897 --> 00:12:58.815
Why not hire them.
take the weekend off?

129
00:12:58.982 --> 00:13:01.818
That wasn't exactly
what I had in mind...

130
00:13:01.985 --> 00:13:03.737
...when I said I wanted
to inspire people.

131
00:13:03.904 --> 00:13:05.822
I know.

132
00:13:05.989 --> 00:13:07.491
But things have improved.

133
00:13:07.699 --> 00:13:10.160
Look at the new district attorney.

134
00:13:10.827 --> 00:13:12.829
I am. closely.

135
00:13:12.996 --> 00:13:14.915
Need to know if he can be trusted.

136
00:13:15.082 --> 00:13:19.127
Are you interested in his character
or his social circle?

137
00:13:22.965 --> 00:13:25.342
Who Rachel spends her time with
is her business.

138
00:13:27.135 --> 00:13:29.388
I trust you don't have me followed
on my day off.

139
00:13:29.555 --> 00:13:31.640
If you ever took one. I might.

140
00:13:33.475 --> 00:13:35.352
Know your limits. Master Wayne.

141
00:13:35.519 --> 00:13:38.647
Batman has no limits.

142
00:13:38.814 --> 00:13:41.859
- Well. you do. sir.
- Well. can't afford to know them.

143
00:13:42.025 --> 00:13:44.528
And what's gonna happen
on the day that you find out?

144
00:13:44.695 --> 00:13:47.406
We all know how much you like to say
"I told you so."

145
00:13:47.573 --> 00:13:50.909
On that day. Master Wayne.
even I won't want to.

146
00:13:51.076 --> 00:13:52.536
Probably.

147
00:13:59.376 --> 00:14:01.044
Sorry I'm late. folks.

148
00:14:01.211 --> 00:14:02.254
DOOR CLOSES

149
00:14:04.965 --> 00:14:07.175
- Where were you?
- Worried you'd have to step up?

150
00:14:07.342 --> 00:14:10.345
- Harvey. I know these briefs backwards.
- Well. then...

151
00:14:10.512 --> 00:14:12.514
...fair's fair.

152
00:14:12.681 --> 00:14:14.725
Heads. I'll take it. Tails. he's all yours.

153
00:14:14.892 --> 00:14:16.977
Yeah? You wanna
flip a coin to see who leads?

154
00:14:17.144 --> 00:14:20.564
My father's lucky coin. As I recall.
it got me my first date with you.

155
00:14:20.731 --> 00:14:23.901
I wouldn't leave something like that
up to chance.

156
00:14:24.234 --> 00:14:27.321
I don't. I make my own luck.

157
00:14:28.822 --> 00:14:32.868
All rise.
The Honorable Judge Freel presiding.

158
00:14:33.035 --> 00:14:35.704
I thought the DA just
played golf with the mayor.

159
00:14:35.871 --> 00:14:39.583
Teeoff's 1:30. More than enough time
to put you away for life. Sally.

160
00:14:39.750 --> 00:14:41.293
With Carmine Falcone in Arkham...

161
00:14:41.460 --> 00:14:44.463
...someone must have stepped up
to run the so-called family.

162
00:14:45.339 --> 00:14:47.591
Is that man in this courtroom today?

163
00:14:49.134 --> 00:14:52.763
- Could you identify him for us. please?
- You win. counselor.

164
00:14:55.098 --> 00:14:56.600
It was me.

165
00:14:58.310 --> 00:15:02.105
I have a sworn statement from you
that this man...

166
00:15:02.272 --> 00:15:05.984
...Salvatore Maroni. is the new head
of the Falcone crime family.

167
00:15:06.151 --> 00:15:10.280
Maroni? He's a fall guy.
I'm the brains of the organization.

168
00:15:11.657 --> 00:15:13.200
Order.
- Permission to treat...

169
00:15:13.367 --> 00:15:14.618
...the witness as hostile?
- Granted.

170
00:15:14.785 --> 00:15:15.827
Hostile? I'll show you hostile!

171
00:15:22.042 --> 00:15:24.795
Carbon fiber..28 caliber.
made in China.

172
00:15:24.962 --> 00:15:26.505
If you wanna kill a
public servant. Mr. Maroni...

173
00:15:26.672 --> 00:15:28.882
...I recommend you buy American.

174
00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:32.427
Get him out of here.
- But. Your Honor. I'm not done.

175
00:15:36.139 --> 00:15:39.434
We'll never be able to link the gun
to Maroni. so we can't charge him.

176
00:15:39.601 --> 00:15:42.396
But they're trying to kill you.
means we're getting to them.

177
00:15:42.563 --> 00:15:45.691
I'm glad you're so pleased. Rachel.
I'm fine. by the way.

178
00:15:45.858 --> 00:15:47.568
Come on. Harvey. You're Gotham's DA.

179
00:15:47.734 --> 00:15:50.571
You're not getting shot at.
you're not doing your job right.

180
00:15:50.737 --> 00:15:51.947
But. you know...

181
00:15:52.114 --> 00:15:55.450
...if you said you were rattled.
we could take the rest of the day off.

182
00:15:55.617 --> 00:15:58.537
Can't. I dragged the head of
the Major Crimes Unit down here.

183
00:15:58.704 --> 00:16:03.458
Oh. Jim Gordon? He's a friend. actually.
Try to be nice.

184
00:16:12.509 --> 00:16:15.304
I hear you got a hell of a right cross.

185
00:16:18.599 --> 00:16:20.726
It's a shame Sal's going to walk.

186
00:16:20.893 --> 00:16:24.938
Yeah. well. good thing about the Mob
is they keep giving you second chances.

187
00:16:30.110 --> 00:16:32.446
Lightly irradiated bills.

188
00:16:32.905 --> 00:16:35.199
Fancy stuff for a city cop. Have help?

189
00:16:35.657 --> 00:16:37.367
We liaise with various agencies...

190
00:16:37.534 --> 00:16:39.286
Save it. Gordon. I wanna meet him.

191
00:16:39.453 --> 00:16:43.040
Official policy is to arrest the vigilante
known as Batman on sight.

192
00:16:43.207 --> 00:16:45.375
What about that floodlight
on the top of MCU?

193
00:16:45.542 --> 00:16:47.961
If you got problems
with malfunctioning equipment...

194
00:16:48.128 --> 00:16:51.340
...I suggest you take them up
with Maintenance. counselor.

195
00:16:51.632 --> 00:16:54.176
I've put every money launderer
in Gotham behind bars...

196
00:16:54.343 --> 00:16:56.720
...but the Mob
is still getting its money out.

197
00:16:56.887 --> 00:17:00.349
I think you and your friend
have found the last game in town.

198
00:17:00.515 --> 00:17:03.227
You're trying to hit them
where it hurts. their wallets.

199
00:17:03.393 --> 00:17:04.561
It's bold.

200
00:17:05.604 --> 00:17:06.647
You gonna count me in?

201
00:17:07.189 --> 00:17:10.567
In this town. the fewer people know
something. the safer the operation.

202
00:17:10.734 --> 00:17:12.986
I don't like that you got
your own special unit...

203
00:17:13.153 --> 00:17:16.073
...and it's full of cops
I investigated at Internal Affairs.

204
00:17:16.240 --> 00:17:19.076
If I didn't work with cops
you'd investigated while at IA...

205
00:17:19.243 --> 00:17:20.494
...I'd be working alone.

206
00:17:21.245 --> 00:17:23.163
I don't get political points
for being an idealist.

207
00:17:23.330 --> 00:17:25.749
I do the best I can with what I have.

208
00:17:29.336 --> 00:17:33.090
You want me to back warrants
for search and seizure on five banks...

209
00:17:33.257 --> 00:17:35.092
...without telling me what we're after.

210
00:17:36.176 --> 00:17:38.762
I can give you the names of the banks.

211
00:17:38.929 --> 00:17:40.847
Well. that's a start.

212
00:17:41.223 --> 00:17:43.559
I'll get you your warrants.
but I want your trust.

213
00:17:43.725 --> 00:17:45.394
Oh. you don't have
to sell me. Dent.

214
00:17:45.561 --> 00:17:47.563
We all know you're Gotham's
white knight.

215
00:17:48.814 --> 00:17:52.276
Yeah. well. I heard they have
a different name for me down at MCU.

216
00:17:52.860 --> 00:17:54.152
I wouldn't know about that.

217
00:17:55.320 --> 00:17:59.116
In China. Lau Security Investments
stands for dynamic new growth.

218
00:17:59.283 --> 00:18:03.579
A joint Chinese venture with
Wayne Enterprises will be a powerhouse.

219
00:18:03.745 --> 00:18:05.664
Well. Mr. Lau...

220
00:18:06.039 --> 00:18:08.792
...I speak for the rest of the board...

221
00:18:09.376 --> 00:18:12.296
...and Mr. Wayne.
in expressing our own excitement.

222
00:18:17.175 --> 00:18:20.804
Sir. I know Mr. Wayne is curious about
how his trust fund gets replenished...

223
00:18:20.971 --> 00:18:23.473
...but. frankly. this is embarrassing.

224
00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:26.226
You worry about the diligence.
Mr. Reese.

225
00:18:26.393 --> 00:18:28.687
I'll worry about Bruce Wayne.

226
00:18:28.854 --> 00:18:30.397
It's done.

227
00:18:30.564 --> 00:18:32.316
The numbers are solid.

228
00:18:32.482 --> 00:18:34.026
Do them again.

229
00:18:34.193 --> 00:18:37.279
Wouldn't want the trust fund to run out.
now. would we?

230
00:18:39.990 --> 00:18:41.617
Another long night?

231
00:18:41.783 --> 00:18:44.745
This joint venture was your idea.
and the consultants love it.

232
00:18:45.412 --> 00:18:46.663
But I'm not convinced.

233
00:18:46.830 --> 00:18:50.500
Lau's company has grown by
8 percent annually like clockwork.

234
00:18:50.667 --> 00:18:53.086
His revenue stream
must be off the books...

235
00:18:53.253 --> 00:18:54.671
...maybe even illegal.

236
00:18:54.838 --> 00:18:56.506
Okay. Cancel the deal.

237
00:18:57.841 --> 00:18:59.009
You already knew.

238
00:18:59.718 --> 00:19:02.262
Just needed a closer look at their books.

239
00:19:02.429 --> 00:19:04.473
Anything else you can trouble me for?

240
00:19:04.932 --> 00:19:06.475
I need a new suit.

241
00:19:06.642 --> 00:19:09.144
Yeah. Three buttons
is a little '90s. Mr. Wayne.

242
00:19:09.311 --> 00:19:12.439
I'm not talking fashion. Mr. Fox.
so much as function.

243
00:19:13.482 --> 00:19:15.192
You wanna be able to turn your head.

244
00:19:15.359 --> 00:19:17.444
Sure make backing out
of the driveway easier.

245
00:19:17.903 --> 00:19:19.446
I'll see what I can do.

246
00:19:24.201 --> 00:19:26.161
Took three weeks
to get a reservation here.

247
00:19:26.328 --> 00:19:28.455
I had to tell them
I work for the government.

248
00:19:28.622 --> 00:19:29.873
- Really?
- Health inspector's...

249
00:19:30.040 --> 00:19:31.291
...not afraid to pull strings.

250
00:19:31.458 --> 00:19:33.669
Rachel. Fancy that.

251
00:19:33.835 --> 00:19:36.338
Yeah. Bruce. Fancy that.

252
00:19:36.672 --> 00:19:38.840
Rachel. Natascha. Natascha. Rachel.

253
00:19:39.007 --> 00:19:44.388
- Natascha. Are you the prima...?
- Prima ballerina for the Moscow Ballet.

254
00:19:44.555 --> 00:19:47.891
- Wow. Harvey's taking me next week.
- Really? So you're into ballet?

255
00:19:48.225 --> 00:19:50.394
Bruce. This is Harvey Dent.

256
00:19:50.727 --> 00:19:54.481
The famous Bruce Wayne.
Rachel's told me everything about you.

257
00:19:54.648 --> 00:19:55.858
I certainly hope not.

258
00:19:56.191 --> 00:19:59.528
- Let's put a couple tables together.
- I'm not sure that they'll let us.

259
00:19:59.695 --> 00:20:02.739
Oh. they should. I own the place.

260
00:20:03.198 --> 00:20:06.159
How could you want to raise children
in a city like this?

261
00:20:06.326 --> 00:20:08.287
Well. I was raised here.
I turned out okay.

262
00:20:08.453 --> 00:20:10.038
Is Wayne Manor in the city limits?

263
00:20:10.205 --> 00:20:11.707
Is...?

264
00:20:11.874 --> 00:20:13.417
The Palisades? Sure.

265
00:20:13.584 --> 00:20:16.044
You know. as our new DA.
you might wanna figure out...

266
00:20:16.211 --> 00:20:18.046
...where your jurisdiction ends.

267
00:20:18.213 --> 00:20:22.175
I'm talking about the kind of city
that idolizes a masked vigilante.

268
00:20:22.342 --> 00:20:25.721
Gotham City is proud of an ordinary
citizen standing up for what's right.

269
00:20:25.888 --> 00:20:28.140
Gotham needs heroes like you.
elected officials...

270
00:20:28.307 --> 00:20:30.267
...not a man who thinks
he's above the law.

271
00:20:30.434 --> 00:20:31.602
Who appointed the Batman?

272
00:20:31.768 --> 00:20:35.606
We did. All of us who stood by
and let scum take control of our city.

273
00:20:35.772 --> 00:20:37.524
But this is a democracy. Harvey.

274
00:20:37.691 --> 00:20:39.443
When their enemies were at the gates...

275
00:20:39.610 --> 00:20:43.322
...the Romans would suspend democracy
and appoint one man to protect the city.

276
00:20:43.488 --> 00:20:46.074
It wasn't considered an honor.
it was a public service.

277
00:20:46.241 --> 00:20:47.910
Harvey. the last man
that they appointed...

278
00:20:48.076 --> 00:20:50.370
...to protect the republic
was named Caesar...

279
00:20:50.537 --> 00:20:53.957
...and he never gave up his power.
- Okay. fine.

280
00:20:54.124 --> 00:20:55.459
You either die a hero...

281
00:20:55.626 --> 00:20:58.670
...or you live long enough
to see yourself become the villain.

282
00:20:58.837 --> 00:21:02.341
Whoever the Batman is. he doesn't
wanna do this for the rest of his life.

283
00:21:02.507 --> 00:21:05.761
How could he? Batman is looking for
someone to take up his mantle.

284
00:21:05.928 --> 00:21:08.222
Someone like you. Mr. Dent?

285
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:11.141
Maybe. If I'm up to it.

286
00:21:11.308 --> 00:21:16.563
What if Harvey Dent
is the Caped Crusader? Hm?

287
00:21:18.815 --> 00:21:21.985
If I were sneaking out every night.
someone would've noticed by now.

288
00:21:24.363 --> 00:21:28.492
Well. I'm sold. Dent.
and I'm gonna throw you a fundraiser.

289
00:21:28.659 --> 00:21:31.495
That's nice. but I'm not
up for reelection for three years.

290
00:21:31.662 --> 00:21:33.580
No. you don't understand.

291
00:21:33.747 --> 00:21:36.542
One fundraiser with my pals...

292
00:21:37.167 --> 00:21:39.294
...you'll never need another cent.

293
00:21:54.017 --> 00:21:56.144
What the hell is this?

294
00:21:57.479 --> 00:22:00.607
As you're all aware.
one of our deposits was stolen.

295
00:22:00.774 --> 00:22:04.152
A relatively small amount. 68 million.

296
00:22:04.319 --> 00:22:06.864
Who's stupid enough to steal from us?

297
00:22:07.197 --> 00:22:10.742
Two-bit wackjob.
wears a cheap purple suit and makeup.

298
00:22:10.909 --> 00:22:12.870
He's not the problem. He's a nobody.

299
00:22:13.036 --> 00:22:16.415
The problem is our money
being tracked by the cops.

300
00:22:16.582 --> 00:22:19.084
Thanks to Mr. Maroni's
well-placed sources...

301
00:22:19.251 --> 00:22:23.046
...we know that police have indeed
identified our banks using marked bills...

302
00:22:23.213 --> 00:22:25.716
...and are planning to
seize your funds today.

303
00:22:25.883 --> 00:22:29.887
And since the enthusiastic new D A has
put all my competitors out of business...

304
00:22:30.512 --> 00:22:34.016
...I'm your only option.
So. what are you proposing?

305
00:22:34.183 --> 00:22:37.853
Moving all deposits to
one secure location. not a bank.

306
00:22:38.020 --> 00:22:39.980
- Where. then?
- No one can know but me.

307
00:22:40.731 --> 00:22:43.483
If the police were to gain leverage
over one of you...

308
00:22:43.650 --> 00:22:45.444
...everyone's money would be at stake.

309
00:22:45.611 --> 00:22:47.738
What stop them getting to you?

310
00:22:47.905 --> 00:22:50.991
I go to Hong Kong.
far from Dent's jurisdiction...

311
00:22:51.366 --> 00:22:54.244
...and the Chinese will not extradite
one of their own.

312
00:22:54.411 --> 00:22:56.038
How soon can you move the money?

313
00:22:56.330 --> 00:22:57.414
I already have.

314
00:22:59.791 --> 00:23:02.419
For obvious reasons. I couldn't wait
for your permission.

315
00:23:03.045 --> 00:23:06.715
Rest assured. your money is safe.

316
00:23:19.061 --> 00:23:21.313
And I thought my jokes were bad.

317
00:23:21.480 --> 00:23:24.566
Give me one reason why I shouldn't
have my boy pull your head off.

318
00:23:24.733 --> 00:23:26.026
How about a magic trick?

319
00:23:29.363 --> 00:23:31.698
I'm gonna make this pencil disappear.

320
00:23:33.992 --> 00:23:35.118
Ta-da!

321
00:23:35.285 --> 00:23:36.787
It's...

322
00:23:36.954 --> 00:23:39.248
It's gone.

323
00:23:39.623 --> 00:23:41.959
Oh. and by the way.
the suit. it wasn't cheap.

324
00:23:42.125 --> 00:23:44.962
- You ought to know. you bought it.
Sit.

325
00:23:46.046 --> 00:23:49.091
I want to hear proposition.

326
00:23:51.802 --> 00:23:54.304
Let's wind the clocks back a year.

327
00:23:54.638 --> 00:24:00.310
These cops and lawyers
wouldn't dare cross any of you.

328
00:24:01.478 --> 00:24:03.605
I mean. what happened?

329
00:24:03.772 --> 00:24:07.568
Did your balls drop off? Hm?

330
00:24:07.734 --> 00:24:09.778
You see. a guy like me...

331
00:24:10.237 --> 00:24:12.990
- A freak.
Damn right.

332
00:24:13.156 --> 00:24:16.285
A guy like me... Look. listen.

333
00:24:16.827 --> 00:24:21.123
I know why you choose
to have your little. ahem...

334
00:24:21.290 --> 00:24:24.001
...group-therapy sessions
in broad daylight.

335
00:24:24.501 --> 00:24:27.296
I know why you're afraid
to go out at night.

336
00:24:29.506 --> 00:24:31.174
The Batman.

337
00:24:31.341 --> 00:24:36.597
See. Batman has shown Gotham
your true colors. unfortunately.

338
00:24:36.763 --> 00:24:40.267
Dent. he's just the beginning.

339
00:24:40.851 --> 00:24:45.606
And as for the television's
so-called plan...

340
00:24:46.064 --> 00:24:47.941
...Batman has no jurisdiction.

341
00:24:48.108 --> 00:24:50.694
He'll find him and make him squeal.

342
00:24:50.861 --> 00:24:53.864
I know the squealers when I see them...

343
00:24:54.031 --> 00:24:55.699
...and...

344
00:24:56.450 --> 00:24:57.951
What do you propose?

345
00:24:58.118 --> 00:25:00.537
It's simple. We. uh. kill the Batman.

346
00:25:01.872 --> 00:25:04.833
If it's so simple. why haven't
you done it already?

347
00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:07.711
If you're good at something.
never do it for free.

348
00:25:08.378 --> 00:25:09.671
How much you want?

349
00:25:10.380 --> 00:25:12.382
Uh. half.

350
00:25:14.593 --> 00:25:17.346
You're crazy.
- No. I'm not.

351
00:25:17.512 --> 00:25:19.640
No. I'm not.

352
00:25:21.225 --> 00:25:24.645
If we don't deal with this now...

353
00:25:24.811 --> 00:25:26.438
...soon...

354
00:25:26.647 --> 00:25:31.568
...little Gambol here won't be able
to get a nickel for his grandma.

355
00:25:32.236 --> 00:25:33.695
Enough from the clown!

356
00:25:33.862 --> 00:25:36.823
Ah. ta-ta-ta. Let's not blow...

357
00:25:36.990 --> 00:25:39.535
Shit!
...this out of proportion.

358
00:25:39.701 --> 00:25:42.204
You think you can steal from us
and just walk away?

359
00:25:42.371 --> 00:25:43.914
- Yeah.
I'm putting the word out.

360
00:25:44.081 --> 00:25:46.375
Five hundred grand for this clown dead.

361
00:25:46.542 --> 00:25:49.586
A million alive. so I can teach him
some manners first.

362
00:25:50.879 --> 00:25:53.465
All right. So. listen.
why don't you give me a call...

363
00:25:53.632 --> 00:25:57.386
...when you wanna start taking things
a little more seriously?

364
00:25:57.553 --> 00:25:59.429
Here's my card.

365
00:26:19.533 --> 00:26:21.910
You're a hard man to reach.

366
00:26:24.913 --> 00:26:27.207
Lau's halfway to Hong Kong.

367
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:31.336
If you'd have asked.
I could have taken his passport.

368
00:26:31.503 --> 00:26:34.172
All that was left in the vaults
were marked bills.

369
00:26:34.339 --> 00:26:37.634
They knew we were coming.
As soon as your office got involved...

370
00:26:37.801 --> 00:26:38.844
My office?

371
00:26:39.011 --> 00:26:42.681
You're sitting down there with scum like
Wuertz and Ramirez and you're talking...

372
00:26:42.848 --> 00:26:45.976
Oh. yeah. I almost had your rookie
cold on a racketeering beat.

373
00:26:46.143 --> 00:26:50.689
Don't try and cloud the fact that clearly
Maroni's got people in your office. Dent.

374
00:26:53.483 --> 00:26:55.444
We need Lau back...

375
00:26:55.611 --> 00:26:59.573
...but the Chinese won't extradite
a national under any circumstances.

376
00:26:59.907 --> 00:27:02.618
If I get him to you.
can you get him to talk?

377
00:27:02.784 --> 00:27:03.994
I'll get him to sing.

378
00:27:04.161 --> 00:27:06.914
We're going after the Mob's life savings.

379
00:27:07.080 --> 00:27:08.332
Things will get ugly.

380
00:27:08.498 --> 00:27:10.792
I knew the risk when I took this job.
lieutenant.

381
00:27:10.959 --> 00:27:12.502
How will you get him back. any...?

382
00:27:15.088 --> 00:27:16.506
He does that.

383
00:27:16.673 --> 00:27:20.177
Our Chinese friends left town
before I could tell them the deal was off.

384
00:27:20.344 --> 00:27:23.847
Well. I'm sure that you've always
wanted to go to Hong Kong.

385
00:27:24.014 --> 00:27:26.183
What's wrong with a phone call?

386
00:27:26.350 --> 00:27:29.978
I think Mr. Lau deserves
a more personal touch.

387
00:27:31.188 --> 00:27:33.023
Now. for high-altitude jumps...

388
00:27:33.190 --> 00:27:35.984
...you're going to need oxygen
and stabilizers.

389
00:27:36.151 --> 00:27:39.780
Well. I must say.
compared to your usual requests...

390
00:27:39.947 --> 00:27:42.533
...jumping out of an airplane
is pretty straightforward.

391
00:27:43.158 --> 00:27:45.285
What about getting back into the plane?

392
00:27:45.452 --> 00:27:49.289
- I'd recommend a good travel agent.
- Without it landing.

393
00:27:50.457 --> 00:27:53.210
Now. that's more like it. Mr. Wayne.

394
00:27:53.752 --> 00:27:56.380
The CIA had a program
back in the '60s...

395
00:27:56.547 --> 00:27:59.883
...for getting their people out
of hot spots called Sky Hook.

396
00:28:00.050 --> 00:28:02.719
- We could look into that.
- Yeah.

397
00:28:02.886 --> 00:28:04.555
Okay. Now...

398
00:28:06.056 --> 00:28:08.767
Hardened Kevlar plates
over titanium-dipped...

399
00:28:08.934 --> 00:28:11.061
...tri-weave fibers for flexibility.

400
00:28:11.228 --> 00:28:14.064
You'll be lighter. faster. more agile.

401
00:28:17.568 --> 00:28:19.736
Perhaps you should
read the instructions first?

402
00:28:19.903 --> 00:28:21.905
- Yeah.
- Now. there is a tradeoff.

403
00:28:22.072 --> 00:28:25.576
Separation of the plates makes you
more vulnerable to knives and gunfire.

404
00:28:25.742 --> 00:28:28.704
We wouldn't wanna make things
too easy. now. would we?

405
00:28:28.871 --> 00:28:30.914
How will it hold up against dogs?

406
00:28:31.081 --> 00:28:33.208
We talking rottweilers or Chihuahuas?

407
00:28:34.418 --> 00:28:36.920
Should do fine against cats.

408
00:28:37.087 --> 00:28:39.214
I found one in Arizona.

409
00:28:39.381 --> 00:28:42.301
A very nice man said he could have it
up and running in a week...

410
00:28:42.467 --> 00:28:43.552
...and he takes cash.

411
00:28:43.719 --> 00:28:46.555
- What about the flight crew?
- South Korean smugglers.

412
00:28:46.722 --> 00:28:48.932
They run flights into Pyongyang.
below radar.

413
00:28:49.099 --> 00:28:51.852
- Did you think of an alibi?
- Oh. yes.

414
00:29:10.621 --> 00:29:13.248
I believe this is your plane. sir.

415
00:29:17.461 --> 00:29:20.964
You look tired. Alfred.
You'll be all right without me?

416
00:29:22.633 --> 00:29:26.136
If you can tell me the Russian for
"apply your own bloody suntan lotion."

417
00:29:37.272 --> 00:29:41.109
Yo. Gambol. somebody here for you.
They say they've just killed the Joker.

418
00:29:41.276 --> 00:29:43.111
They brought the body.

419
00:29:59.503 --> 00:30:02.005
So. dead. that's 500.

420
00:30:03.966 --> 00:30:05.759
How about alive? Hm?

421
00:30:08.971 --> 00:30:12.140
You wanna know how I got these scars?

422
00:30:14.059 --> 00:30:17.062
My father was...

423
00:30:17.229 --> 00:30:18.689
...a drinker...

424
00:30:18.856 --> 00:30:20.107
...and a fiend.

425
00:30:20.941 --> 00:30:25.112
And one night.
he goes off crazier than usual.

426
00:30:25.529 --> 00:30:28.323
Mommy gets the kitchen knife
to defend herself.

427
00:30:28.490 --> 00:30:30.033
He doesn't like that...

428
00:30:30.200 --> 00:30:33.662
...not one bit.

429
00:30:33.829 --> 00:30:36.373
So. me watching...

430
00:30:36.540 --> 00:30:41.128
...he takes the knife to her.
laughing while he does it.

431
00:30:41.295 --> 00:30:44.381
He turns to me and he says:

432
00:30:44.548 --> 00:30:48.218
"Why so serious?"

433
00:30:48.468 --> 00:30:50.053
He comes at me with the knife.

434
00:30:50.721 --> 00:30:52.639
"Why so serious?"

435
00:30:54.892 --> 00:30:57.769
He sticks the blade in my mouth.

436
00:30:58.103 --> 00:31:02.024
"Let's put a smile on that face."

437
00:31:03.233 --> 00:31:05.444
And...

438
00:31:07.821 --> 00:31:09.364
Why so serious?

439
00:31:14.411 --> 00:31:15.913
Now...

440
00:31:16.079 --> 00:31:18.332
...our operation is small...

441
00:31:18.498 --> 00:31:21.418
...but there is a lot of potential...

442
00:31:21.585 --> 00:31:24.129
...for aggressive expansion.

443
00:31:24.296 --> 00:31:27.507
So which of you fine gentlemen
would like to join our team?

444
00:31:27.674 --> 00:31:32.095
Oh. There's only one spot open
right now. so we're gonna have...

445
00:31:32.763 --> 00:31:34.932
...tryouts.

446
00:31:39.520 --> 00:31:41.522
Make it fast.

447
00:31:50.948 --> 00:31:52.366
Welcome to Hong Kong. Mr. Fox.

448
00:31:52.533 --> 00:31:55.244
Mr. Lau regrets he is unable
to greet you in person today.

449
00:31:55.410 --> 00:31:57.329
I understand.

450
00:32:07.130 --> 00:32:10.717
For security purposes. I'm gonna have to
ask you to check in your mobile.

451
00:32:10.884 --> 00:32:12.469
Of course.

452
00:32:15.222 --> 00:32:18.934
I must apologize for leaving Gotham
in the middle of our negotiations.

453
00:32:19.101 --> 00:32:22.646
This misunderstanding
with the Gotham police force...

454
00:32:22.813 --> 00:32:25.357
...I couldn't let it threaten my company.
- Of course.

455
00:32:25.524 --> 00:32:28.694
A businessman of your stature
will understand and...

456
00:32:28.861 --> 00:32:32.823
...with you here now. we can continue.

457
00:32:32.990 --> 00:32:36.743
Well. I do appreciate you bringing me
out here in such style. Mr. Lau. but I re...

458
00:32:38.287 --> 00:32:40.122
We do not allow cell phones in here.

459
00:32:40.289 --> 00:32:43.000
I'm sorry. Forgot I had it.

460
00:32:43.166 --> 00:32:47.796
No. I really came to tell you that
our business deal has to be put on hold.

461
00:32:48.338 --> 00:32:51.425
You see. we can't afford
to be seen to do business with...

462
00:32:52.551 --> 00:32:54.511
...whatever it is you're accused of being.

463
00:32:54.678 --> 00:32:57.264
I'm sure a businessman of your stature
will understand.

464
00:32:57.431 --> 00:33:01.351
I think. Mr. Fox. a simple phone call
might have sufficed.

465
00:33:01.518 --> 00:33:04.897
Mr. Wayne didn't want you to think
he was deliberately wasting your time.

466
00:33:05.063 --> 00:33:06.690
Just accidentally wasting it.

467
00:33:07.691 --> 00:33:11.862
That's very good. Mr. Lau.
"Accidentally." Very good.

468
00:33:12.654 --> 00:33:13.989
Hey. sir.

469
00:33:32.216 --> 00:33:34.218
There's a better view
from the peak tram.

470
00:33:34.384 --> 00:33:36.220
How's the view from LSI Holdings?

471
00:33:36.512 --> 00:33:38.055
Restricted.

472
00:33:38.222 --> 00:33:40.224
Lau is holed up in there good and tight.

473
00:33:40.390 --> 00:33:42.309
- What's this?
- I had R & D work it up.

474
00:33:42.476 --> 00:33:44.144
Sends out a high-frequency pulse...

475
00:33:44.311 --> 00:33:47.147
...records the response time
for mapping an environment.

476
00:33:47.648 --> 00:33:50.234
Sonar. Just like a...

477
00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:52.569
Submarine. Mr. Wayne.
Like a submarine.

478
00:33:53.070 --> 00:33:54.905
- And the other device?
- It's in place.

479
00:33:55.822 --> 00:33:56.865
Mr. Wayne?

480
00:33:58.075 --> 00:33:59.368
Good luck.

481
00:37:49.348 --> 00:37:52.518
Look. give us the money
and we'll talk about making a deal.

482
00:37:52.684 --> 00:37:55.979
The money is the only reason
I'm still alive.

483
00:37:56.146 --> 00:38:00.275
Oh. you mean. when they find out that
you've helped us. they're gonna kill you?

484
00:38:00.442 --> 00:38:02.152
- Are you threatening my client?
- No.

485
00:38:02.319 --> 00:38:06.532
I'm just assuming your client's
cooperation with this investigation.

486
00:38:08.158 --> 00:38:09.826
As will everyone.

487
00:38:11.161 --> 00:38:14.498
No? Okay.

488
00:38:14.957 --> 00:38:17.960
Enjoy your time in County. Mr. Lau.

489
00:38:18.126 --> 00:38:19.628
Wait!

490
00:38:19.836 --> 00:38:21.838
I won't give you the money...

491
00:38:22.005 --> 00:38:25.008
...but I will give you my clients.
all of them.

492
00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:27.511
You were a glorified accountant.

493
00:38:27.678 --> 00:38:31.515
What could you possibly have
on all of them that we could charge?

494
00:38:31.682 --> 00:38:35.519
I'm good with calculation.
I handled all their investments.

495
00:38:35.686 --> 00:38:37.271
One big pot.

496
00:38:38.647 --> 00:38:39.982
Got it.

497
00:38:40.399 --> 00:38:42.234
One minute.

498
00:38:43.026 --> 00:38:45.737
If they pooled their money...

499
00:38:45.904 --> 00:38:47.698
...we can charge them
as one criminal conspiracy.

500
00:38:47.865 --> 00:38:49.032
Charge them with what?

501
00:38:49.199 --> 00:38:52.077
In a RICO case. if you can charge
one of them with a felony...

502
00:38:52.244 --> 00:38:54.830
You can charge all of them with it.
That's great.

503
00:38:56.206 --> 00:38:58.125
Mr. Lau.

504
00:38:59.126 --> 00:39:03.130
What kind of details do you have
about this communal fund?

505
00:39:03.297 --> 00:39:04.923
- Ledgers...?
- Immunity. protection...

506
00:39:05.090 --> 00:39:08.552
...a chartered plane back to Hong Kong.
- After you testify in open court.

507
00:39:08.719 --> 00:39:11.054
I'm just curious.
With all your clients locked up...

508
00:39:11.388 --> 00:39:13.599
...what's gonna happen
with all that money?

509
00:39:13.765 --> 00:39:16.894
Like I said. I'm good with calculation.

510
00:39:17.060 --> 00:39:21.732
He can't go to County.
I'll keep him here in the holding cells.

511
00:39:21.899 --> 00:39:24.443
What is this. Gordon. your fortress?

512
00:39:24.735 --> 00:39:27.404
Well. you trust them over at County?

513
00:39:27.571 --> 00:39:29.406
I don't trust them here.

514
00:39:31.158 --> 00:39:32.659
Lau stays.

515
00:39:33.118 --> 00:39:35.704
Well. I don 't know about
Mr. Lau's travel arrangements...

516
00:39:35.871 --> 00:39:37.664
...but I'm sure glad he's back.

517
00:39:37.831 --> 00:39:40.292
Put word out. We hire the clown.

518
00:39:43.086 --> 00:39:46.924
He was right.
We have to fix real problem.

519
00:39:47.424 --> 00:39:48.550
Batman.

520
00:39:53.096 --> 00:39:57.017
- I'm not aware of any participation...
- Our boy looks good on the tube.

521
00:39:57.518 --> 00:40:00.270
You sure you wanna embarrass me
in front of my friends?

522
00:40:00.437 --> 00:40:04.107
Oh. don't worry. They're coming too.

523
00:40:10.948 --> 00:40:12.783
Have a nice trip. See you next fall.

524
00:40:12.950 --> 00:40:14.785
Seven hundred
twelve counts of extortion.

525
00:40:14.952 --> 00:40:17.371
Eight hundred and forty-nine
counts of racketeering.

526
00:40:17.538 --> 00:40:20.082
Two hundred and forty-six
counts of fraud.

527
00:40:20.249 --> 00:40:23.085
Eighty-seven counts
of conspiracy murder.

528
00:40:24.002 --> 00:40:27.130
Five hundred and twenty-seven
counts of obstruction of justice.

529
00:40:27.548 --> 00:40:28.924
How do the defendants plead?

530
00:40:36.098 --> 00:40:37.140
Order in the court.

531
00:40:37.307 --> 00:40:39.810
Five hundred and forty-nine
criminals at once.

532
00:40:39.977 --> 00:40:42.479
How did you convince Surrillo
to hear this farce?

533
00:40:42.646 --> 00:40:46.775
She shares my enthusiasm for justice.
After all. she is a judge.

534
00:40:46.942 --> 00:40:49.987
Even if you blow enough smoke
to get convictions out of Surrillo...

535
00:40:50.153 --> 00:40:52.739
...you're gonna set
a new record at appeals.

536
00:40:52.906 --> 00:40:55.409
It won't matter.
The head guys make bail. sure.

537
00:40:55.576 --> 00:40:57.995
But the midlevel guys. they can't.

538
00:40:58.161 --> 00:40:59.997
They can't afford to be off the streets.

539
00:41:00.163 --> 00:41:02.291
They'll cut deals that
include some jail time.

540
00:41:02.457 --> 00:41:05.460
Think of all you could do
with 18 months of clean streets.

541
00:41:07.004 --> 00:41:10.132
Mr. Mayor. you can't...
- No. get out. Both of you.

542
00:41:14.303 --> 00:41:15.846
Sit down.

543
00:41:20.809 --> 00:41:23.812
The public likes you. That's the
only reason that this might fly.

544
00:41:23.979 --> 00:41:25.314
But that means it's on you.

545
00:41:25.480 --> 00:41:28.525
They're all gonna come after you now.
and not just the Mob.

546
00:41:28.692 --> 00:41:32.529
Politicians. journalists. cops.

547
00:41:32.696 --> 00:41:35.199
Anyone whose wallet's
about to get lighter.

548
00:41:35.365 --> 00:41:38.035
Are you up to it? You'd better be.

549
00:41:38.202 --> 00:41:40.329
Because they get anything on you...

550
00:41:40.495 --> 00:41:45.292
...and those criminals are back on the
streets. followed swiftly by you and me.

551
00:41:45.459 --> 00:41:46.752
Jesus!

552
00:41:51.215 --> 00:41:53.050
SIRENS WAILING

553
00:42:07.898 --> 00:42:10.359
I think your fundraiser
will be a great success. sir.

554
00:42:10.526 --> 00:42:13.195
And why do you think I wanna
hold a party for Harvey Dent?

555
00:42:13.362 --> 00:42:16.448
I assumed it was your usual reason
for socializing beyond myself...

556
00:42:16.615 --> 00:42:18.659
...and the scum of Gotham's underbelly:

557
00:42:18.825 --> 00:42:20.619
To try to impress Miss Dawes.

558
00:42:20.786 --> 00:42:24.873
Very droll. but very wrong.
Actually. it's Dent.

559
00:42:25.040 --> 00:42:27.918
Police released video
footage found concealed on the body.

560
00:42:28.085 --> 00:42:30.712
Sensitive viewers. be aware.
The image is disturbing.

561
00:42:30.879 --> 00:42:33.090
Tell them your name.

562
00:42:33.257 --> 00:42:34.925
Brian Douglas.

563
00:42:36.510 --> 00:42:38.846
And are you the real Batman?

564
00:42:39.012 --> 00:42:40.055
No.
No?

565
00:42:40.222 --> 00:42:42.182
- No.
- No?

566
00:42:42.349 --> 00:42:44.059
Then why do you dress up like him?

567
00:42:46.812 --> 00:42:50.899
Because he's a symbol that we
don 't have to be afraid of scum like you.

568
00:42:51.066 --> 00:42:54.403
Yeah. You do. Brian. You really do.

569
00:42:58.365 --> 00:43:02.828
So you think Batman 's
made Gotham a better place? Hm?

570
00:43:03.036 --> 00:43:04.580
Look at me.

571
00:43:04.746 --> 00:43:07.040
Look at me!

572
00:43:10.794 --> 00:43:14.298
You see. this is how crazy
Batman 's made Gotham.

573
00:43:14.464 --> 00:43:16.758
You want order in Gotham...

574
00:43:17.092 --> 00:43:21.513
...Batman must take off his mask
and turn himself in.

575
00:43:21.680 --> 00:43:25.475
Oh. and every day he doesn 't.
people will die.

576
00:43:25.809 --> 00:43:27.936
Starting tonight.

577
00:43:28.353 --> 00:43:30.564
I'm a man of my word.

578
00:43:47.831 --> 00:43:50.667
Harvey Dent.
scourge of the underworld...

579
00:43:50.834 --> 00:43:53.921
...scared stiff by the trust-fund brigade.

580
00:43:54.087 --> 00:43:55.339
- I'll be back.
- Rachel.

581
00:43:55.505 --> 00:43:58.342
A little liquid courage. Mr. Dent?

582
00:43:58.509 --> 00:44:00.928
- Thank you. Alfred. right?
- That's right. sir.

583
00:44:01.094 --> 00:44:04.389
Rachel talks about you all the time.
You've known her her whole life.

584
00:44:04.556 --> 00:44:05.807
Not yet. sir.

585
00:44:08.101 --> 00:44:10.354
Any psychotic ex-boyfriends
I should be aware of?

586
00:44:10.521 --> 00:44:12.773
Oh. you have no idea.

587
00:44:31.708 --> 00:44:33.126
I'm sorry that I'm late.

588
00:44:33.293 --> 00:44:35.671
I'm glad to see
that you all got started without me.

589
00:44:35.837 --> 00:44:39.550
Now. where is Harvey? Where...?

590
00:44:39.716 --> 00:44:42.135
Harvey Dent. the man of the hour.

591
00:44:42.302 --> 00:44:43.637
Where's Rachel Dawes?

592
00:44:43.804 --> 00:44:46.181
She is my oldest friend. Come here.

593
00:44:46.348 --> 00:44:48.851
When Rachel first told me she
was dating Harvey Dent...

594
00:44:49.017 --> 00:44:50.227
...I had one thing to say:

595
00:44:50.435 --> 00:44:52.855
"The guy from those God-awful
campaign commercials?"

596
00:44:53.021 --> 00:44:56.859
"I believe in Harvey Dent."
Yeah. nice slogan. Harvey.

597
00:44:57.025 --> 00:44:59.027
But it caught Rachel's attention.

598
00:44:59.194 --> 00:45:02.197
And then I started to pay attention
to Harvey...

599
00:45:02.614 --> 00:45:05.909
...and all that he's been doing
as our new DA.

600
00:45:06.076 --> 00:45:07.870
And you know what?

601
00:45:09.913 --> 00:45:11.415
I believe in Harvey Dent.

602
00:45:11.582 --> 00:45:15.168
I believe that on his watch.
Gotham can feel...

603
00:45:15.335 --> 00:45:19.006
...a little safer. a little more optimistic.

604
00:45:20.424 --> 00:45:24.761
Look at this face. This is the face
of Gotham's bright future.

605
00:45:24.928 --> 00:45:27.097
To Harvey Dent. Let's hear it for him.

606
00:45:27.472 --> 00:45:29.016
Harvey.

607
00:45:38.525 --> 00:45:39.985
Harvey may not know you
well enough...

608
00:45:40.152 --> 00:45:42.112
...to understand you're
making fun of him...

609
00:45:42.279 --> 00:45:44.281
...but I do.
- No. I meant every word.

610
00:45:45.616 --> 00:45:48.535
You know that day
that you once told me about...

611
00:45:48.702 --> 00:45:50.787
...when Gotham would no longer
need Batman?

612
00:45:50.954 --> 00:45:52.873
- It's coming.
- Bruce.

613
00:45:53.707 --> 00:45:59.296
- You can't ask me to wait for that.
- It's happening now. Harvey is that hero.

614
00:45:59.463 --> 00:46:03.926
He locked up half of the city's criminals.
and he did it without wearing a mask.

615
00:46:04.092 --> 00:46:06.303
Gotham needs a hero with a face.

616
00:46:07.137 --> 00:46:09.431
You can throw a party. Wayne.
I'll give you that.

617
00:46:10.807 --> 00:46:12.726
Thanks again.

618
00:46:13.519 --> 00:46:15.229
You mind if I borrow Rachel?

619
00:46:18.690 --> 00:46:21.068
Lieutenant. that joker card
pinned to the body?

620
00:46:21.235 --> 00:46:22.986
Forensics found three sets of DNA.

621
00:46:23.153 --> 00:46:24.571
- Any matches?
- All three.

622
00:46:24.738 --> 00:46:28.242
The DNA belongs to Judge Surrillo.
Harvey Dent and Commissioner Loeb.

623
00:46:28.408 --> 00:46:30.410
The Joker's telling us
who he's targeting.

624
00:46:30.577 --> 00:46:33.455
Get a unit over to Surrillo's house.
Tell Wuertz to find Dent.

625
00:46:33.622 --> 00:46:35.666
Protective custody.
Where's the commissioner?

626
00:46:35.832 --> 00:46:37.334
- City hall.
- Seal the building.

627
00:46:37.501 --> 00:46:39.503
- No one in or out till I get there.
- Got it.

628
00:46:51.807 --> 00:46:54.184
Gordon. What are you up to?

629
00:46:54.351 --> 00:46:57.604
We're secure. I want a floor-by-floor
search of the entire building.

630
00:46:57.771 --> 00:47:00.357
We believe the Joker's
made a threat against your life.

631
00:47:00.524 --> 00:47:01.942
These are dangerous people.

632
00:47:02.109 --> 00:47:03.861
You're not giving me
a lot of information.

633
00:47:04.027 --> 00:47:05.988
Even we don't know
where you're going.

634
00:47:06.154 --> 00:47:09.491
Take the envelope. get in. open it.
It'll tell you where you're headed.

635
00:47:13.328 --> 00:47:15.247
You can't leave me alone
with these people.

636
00:47:15.414 --> 00:47:18.458
The whole Mob's after you
and you're worried about these guys?

637
00:47:18.625 --> 00:47:20.586
Compared to this.
the Mob doesn't scare me.

638
00:47:20.752 --> 00:47:24.339
Gordon. you're unlikely to discover this
for yourself. so...

639
00:47:24.506 --> 00:47:28.594
...take my word. the police commissioner
earns a lot of threats.

640
00:47:28.760 --> 00:47:34.308
I found the appropriate response
to these situations a long time ago.

641
00:47:34.516 --> 00:47:36.768
Them gunning for you
makes you see things clearly.

642
00:47:36.935 --> 00:47:38.270
Yeah. I bet.

643
00:47:38.437 --> 00:47:42.733
Yeah. It makes you think about things
you couldn't stand losing...

644
00:47:42.900 --> 00:47:44.902
...about who you wanna
spend your life with.

645
00:47:45.068 --> 00:47:48.071
- That's a pretty big commitment.
- Not if the Mob has their way.

646
00:47:53.285 --> 00:47:55.996
You get to explain to my wife...

647
00:47:56.914 --> 00:47:58.498
...why I'm late for dinner.

648
00:47:58.665 --> 00:48:01.835
Sir. the joker card
had traces of your DNA on it.

649
00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:06.048
- Don't do that.
- All right.

650
00:48:06.590 --> 00:48:09.510
- Let's be serious. then.
- Okay.

651
00:48:09.843 --> 00:48:10.886
What's your answer?

652
00:48:17.059 --> 00:48:18.560
I don't have an answer.

653
00:48:20.729 --> 00:48:21.772
How'd they get my DNA?

654
00:48:21.939 --> 00:48:24.107
Somebody with access
to your office or house...

655
00:48:24.274 --> 00:48:26.902
...must have lifted a tissue
or a glass... Wait! Wait!

656
00:48:27.069 --> 00:48:29.988
- Well. I guess no answer is a no.
- Harvey.

657
00:48:30.155 --> 00:48:32.282
- It's someone else. isn't it?
- Harvey.

658
00:48:32.449 --> 00:48:35.619
Just tell me it's not Wayne.
The guy's a complete f...

659
00:48:36.119 --> 00:48:37.579
What are you doing?

660
00:48:48.757 --> 00:48:49.800
Oh. shit.

661
00:48:55.973 --> 00:48:57.724
Get a medic!

662
00:49:01.144 --> 00:49:02.271
They've come for him.

663
00:49:03.772 --> 00:49:04.940
We made it.

664
00:49:07.526 --> 00:49:08.569
Stay hidden.

665
00:49:10.821 --> 00:49:14.157
Good evening. ladies and gentlemen.

666
00:49:17.077 --> 00:49:20.998
We are tonight's entertainment.

667
00:49:21.832 --> 00:49:24.167
I only have one question:

668
00:49:24.376 --> 00:49:27.921
Where is Harvey Dent?

669
00:49:37.389 --> 00:49:39.474
You know where Harvey is?
You know who he is?

670
00:49:39.641 --> 00:49:40.934
Hands up. pretty boy.

671
00:49:48.066 --> 00:49:50.861
Do you know where I can find Harvey?
I need to talk to him.

672
00:49:51.028 --> 00:49:53.864
Just something little. huh? No.

673
00:49:56.158 --> 00:49:58.911
What's going on out there? Wayne!

674
00:50:00.370 --> 00:50:01.747
Oh. thank God. you've
got a panic room.

675
00:50:01.914 --> 00:50:03.081
Hey. wait...

676
00:50:03.665 --> 00:50:05.459
Oh. you gotta be kidding me.

677
00:50:05.751 --> 00:50:07.753
You know. I'll settle for his loved ones.

678
00:50:07.920 --> 00:50:11.423
We're not intimidated by thugs.

679
00:50:12.382 --> 00:50:14.092
You know...

680
00:50:15.719 --> 00:50:18.722
...you remind me of my father.

681
00:50:19.181 --> 00:50:21.016
I hated my father.

682
00:50:21.183 --> 00:50:23.227
Okay. stop.

683
00:50:27.064 --> 00:50:29.900
Well. hello. beautiful.

684
00:50:32.069 --> 00:50:35.906
You must be Harvey's squeeze. Hm?

685
00:50:36.281 --> 00:50:38.784
And you are beautiful.

686
00:50:45.707 --> 00:50:49.586
You look nervous. Is it the scars?

687
00:50:50.504 --> 00:50:52.714
You wanna know how I got them?

688
00:50:53.924 --> 00:50:56.468
Come here. Hey.

689
00:50:56.844 --> 00:50:58.554
Look at me.

690
00:50:59.012 --> 00:51:03.767
So I had a wife.
She was beautiful. like you...

691
00:51:04.017 --> 00:51:08.230
...who tells me I worry too much...

692
00:51:08.397 --> 00:51:11.316
...who tells me I ought to smile more...

693
00:51:11.483 --> 00:51:16.989
...who gambles and gets in deep
with the sharks. Hey.

694
00:51:17.406 --> 00:51:19.825
One day they carve her face.

695
00:51:20.325 --> 00:51:24.580
And we have no money for surgeries.
She can't take it.

696
00:51:24.955 --> 00:51:28.458
I just wanna see her smile again. Hm?

697
00:51:28.792 --> 00:51:31.712
I just want her to know
that I don't care about the scars.

698
00:51:32.254 --> 00:51:33.797
So...

699
00:51:34.381 --> 00:51:38.051
...I stick a razor in my mouth
and do this...

700
00:51:38.510 --> 00:51:39.887
...to myself.

701
00:51:40.179 --> 00:51:45.267
And you know what?
She can't stand the sight of me.

702
00:51:45.434 --> 00:51:46.977
She leaves.

703
00:51:47.686 --> 00:51:50.105
Now I see the funny side.

704
00:51:50.981 --> 00:51:52.566
Now I'm always smiling.

705
00:51:55.986 --> 00:51:59.323
You got a little fight in you. I like that.

706
00:51:59.489 --> 00:52:00.824
Then you're gonna love me.

707
00:52:28.977 --> 00:52:30.187
Drop the gun.

708
00:52:30.354 --> 00:52:32.981
Oh. sure. You just take off
your little mask...

709
00:52:33.148 --> 00:52:35.359
...and show us all who
you really are. Hm?

710
00:52:40.989 --> 00:52:42.199
Let her go.

711
00:52:42.991 --> 00:52:44.409
Very poor choice of words.

712
00:53:07.224 --> 00:53:09.101
Are you all right?

713
00:53:11.353 --> 00:53:13.730
Let's not do that again.

714
00:53:14.022 --> 00:53:16.525
- Is Harvey okay?
- He's safe.

715
00:53:18.068 --> 00:53:19.403
Thank you.

716
00:53:19.736 --> 00:53:20.779
Jim. it's over.

717
00:53:20.946 --> 00:53:23.532
As long as they don't get to Lau.
we've cut off their funds.

718
00:53:23.699 --> 00:53:25.200
The prosecution's over.

719
00:53:25.367 --> 00:53:27.035
Nobody's standing up
in front of a judge...

720
00:53:27.202 --> 00:53:30.205
...while judges and police commissioners
are getting blown away.

721
00:53:30.372 --> 00:53:32.165
- What about Dent?
- He's got any sense...

722
00:53:32.332 --> 00:53:33.417
...Dent's halfway to Mex...

723
00:53:33.584 --> 00:53:35.169
So where do you keep your trash?

724
00:53:36.503 --> 00:53:40.465
You're due in court. I need you alive
long enough to get you on the record.

725
00:53:40.632 --> 00:53:43.677
You can't protect me.
You can't even protect yourselves.

726
00:53:43.844 --> 00:53:47.181
You refuse to cooperate. you're not
coming back here. you go to County.

727
00:53:47.347 --> 00:53:49.808
How long do you calculate
you'll last in there?

728
00:53:51.226 --> 00:53:52.728
Targeting me won't get their money.

729
00:53:52.895 --> 00:53:54.730
I knew the Mob wouldn't go
down easily...

730
00:53:54.897 --> 00:53:56.982
...but this is different.
They crossed a line.

731
00:53:57.149 --> 00:53:58.400
You crossed the line first.

732
00:53:58.567 --> 00:54:01.987
You squeezed them. you hammered them
to the point of desperation.

733
00:54:02.154 --> 00:54:07.159
And in their desperation. they turned to
a man they didn't fully understand.

734
00:54:07.659 --> 00:54:10.204
Criminals aren't complicated. Alfred.

735
00:54:10.370 --> 00:54:12.581
We just need to figure out
what he's after.

736
00:54:12.748 --> 00:54:14.166
With respect. Master Wayne...

737
00:54:14.333 --> 00:54:17.294
...perhaps this is a man
you don't fully understand either.

738
00:54:18.086 --> 00:54:20.797
A long time ago. I was in Burma...

739
00:54:20.964 --> 00:54:24.384
...and my friends and I were working
for the local government.

740
00:54:24.551 --> 00:54:27.137
They were trying to buy
the loyalty of tribal leaders...

741
00:54:27.304 --> 00:54:30.140
...by bribing them with
precious stones...

742
00:54:30.307 --> 00:54:34.895
...but their caravans were being raided
in a forest north of Rangoon by a bandit.

743
00:54:35.062 --> 00:54:38.357
So we went looking for the stones.

744
00:54:38.732 --> 00:54:43.862
But in six months. we never
met anyone who traded with him.

745
00:54:44.488 --> 00:54:48.492
One day. I saw a child
playing with a ruby...

746
00:54:48.659 --> 00:54:51.703
...the size of a tangerine.

747
00:54:51.954 --> 00:54:55.332
The bandit had been
throwing them away.

748
00:54:55.999 --> 00:54:58.710
- So why steal them?
- Because he thought it was good sport.

749
00:54:58.877 --> 00:55:03.841
Because some men aren't looking
for anything logical. like money.

750
00:55:04.007 --> 00:55:08.262
They can't be bought. bullied.
reasoned or negotiated with.

751
00:55:08.679 --> 00:55:12.516
Some men just wanna
watch the world burn.

752
00:55:32.953 --> 00:55:34.121
Your name. sir?

753
00:55:34.288 --> 00:55:37.457
Eighth and Orchard.
You'll find Harvey Dent there.

754
00:55:50.345 --> 00:55:51.805
Check the names.

755
00:55:58.395 --> 00:56:00.105
"Richard Dent."

756
00:56:02.316 --> 00:56:03.400
"Patrick Harvey."

757
00:56:03.692 --> 00:56:04.735
Harvey Dent.

758
00:56:04.902 --> 00:56:07.905
I need 10 minutes with the scene
before your men contaminate it.

759
00:56:08.113 --> 00:56:10.324
It's because of you
these guys are dead...

760
00:56:10.490 --> 00:56:12.034
Detective!

761
00:56:14.244 --> 00:56:16.288
Give us a minute. guys.

762
00:56:17.497 --> 00:56:19.082
That's brick underneath.

763
00:56:19.416 --> 00:56:21.084
Gonna take ballistics
off a shattered bullet?

764
00:56:21.251 --> 00:56:22.878
No.

765
00:56:24.338 --> 00:56:26.256
Fingerprints.

766
00:56:34.806 --> 00:56:36.725
Whatever you're gonna do. do it fast.

767
00:56:38.519 --> 00:56:43.232
Because we found his next target.
He's put it in tomorrow's paper.

768
00:57:00.541 --> 00:57:02.835
I'm not sure
you made it loud enough. sir.

769
00:57:15.931 --> 00:57:18.058
What can I do for you. Mr. Reese?

770
00:57:18.225 --> 00:57:22.020
You wanted me to do the diligence
on the LSI Holdings deal again.

771
00:57:22.688 --> 00:57:24.982
Well. I found some irregularities.

772
00:57:25.399 --> 00:57:27.484
Their CEO is in police custody.

773
00:57:27.651 --> 00:57:30.571
No. not with their numbers. with yours.

774
00:57:30.779 --> 00:57:33.866
Applied Sciences. Whole division
of Wayne Enterprises...

775
00:57:34.032 --> 00:57:35.701
...just disappeared overnight.

776
00:57:35.868 --> 00:57:40.122
I went down to the archives
and I started pulling some old files.

777
00:57:41.248 --> 00:57:43.125
Don't tell me you didn't
recognize your baby...

778
00:57:43.292 --> 00:57:46.920
...pancaking cop cars
on the evening news.

779
00:57:47.212 --> 00:57:50.424
Now you got the entire R & D
Department burning through cash...

780
00:57:50.591 --> 00:57:53.927
...claiming it's related to
cell phones for the Army?

781
00:57:54.094 --> 00:57:57.181
What are you building for him now.
a rocket ship?

782
00:57:59.057 --> 00:58:00.809
I want...

783
00:58:00.976 --> 00:58:04.897
...$10 million a year
for the rest of my life.

784
00:58:07.399 --> 00:58:09.526
Let me get this straight.

785
00:58:10.736 --> 00:58:13.197
You think that your client...

786
00:58:13.363 --> 00:58:16.450
One of the wealthiest.
most powerful men in the world...

787
00:58:16.617 --> 00:58:18.202
...is secretly a vigilante...

788
00:58:18.368 --> 00:58:23.040
...who spends his nights beating
criminals to a pulp with his bare hands...

789
00:58:23.207 --> 00:58:26.376
...and your plan
is to blackmail this person?

790
00:58:33.842 --> 00:58:35.135
Good luck.

791
00:58:38.013 --> 00:58:39.431
When...

792
00:58:40.849 --> 00:58:42.309
Keep that.

793
00:58:48.982 --> 00:58:51.443
This is your original scan.

794
00:58:52.861 --> 00:58:55.155
Here it is reengineered.

795
00:59:03.372 --> 00:59:06.917
And there's the thumbprint he left
when he pushed the round in the clip.

796
00:59:08.919 --> 00:59:10.087
I'll get you a copy.

797
00:59:10.295 --> 00:59:14.091
Mr. Wayne. did you reassign R & D?

798
00:59:14.258 --> 00:59:16.760
Yeah. Government
telecommunications project.

799
00:59:16.927 --> 00:59:18.971
Wasn't aware
we had any government contracts.

800
00:59:19.221 --> 00:59:22.224
You know. Lucius. I'm playing this one
pretty close to the chest.

801
00:59:23.350 --> 00:59:25.060
Fair enough.

802
00:59:27.980 --> 00:59:29.439
With no word
from the Batman...

803
00:59:29.606 --> 00:59:31.108
...even as they mourn
Commissioner Loeb...

804
00:59:31.275 --> 00:59:34.653
...these cops have to wonder if
the Joker will make good on his threat...

805
00:59:34.820 --> 00:59:38.031
...in the obituary column of
The Gotham Times to kill the mayor.

806
00:59:39.825 --> 00:59:43.495
I've checked all the databases.
There are four possibles.

807
00:59:43.662 --> 00:59:45.789
Cross-reference the addresses.

808
00:59:45.956 --> 00:59:49.960
Look for Parkside.
overlooking the parade.

809
00:59:51.170 --> 00:59:52.296
I got one.

810
00:59:52.462 --> 00:59:56.466
Melvin White.
1502 Randolph Apartments.

811
00:59:56.842 --> 01:00:00.929
Aggravated assault.
moved to Arkham twice.

812
01:00:40.010 --> 01:00:41.595
What do you got on the roof?

813
01:00:41.762 --> 01:00:45.307
We're tight. but frankly.
there's a lot of windows up here.

814
01:00:53.857 --> 01:00:57.903
Commissioner Loeb dedicated his life
to law enforcement...

815
01:00:58.070 --> 01:01:00.364
...and to the protection
of his community.

816
01:01:00.531 --> 01:01:02.324
I remember when I first took office...

817
01:01:02.491 --> 01:01:05.035
...and I asked if he wanted
to stay on as commissioner.

818
01:01:05.202 --> 01:01:10.457
And he said he would. provided
I kept my politics out of his office.

819
01:01:14.211 --> 01:01:17.381
Clearly he was not a man who minced
words. nor should he have been.

820
01:01:18.549 --> 01:01:22.052
A number of policies that he enacted
as commissioner were unpopular.

821
01:01:22.219 --> 01:01:25.472
Policies that flooded my office
with angry calls and letters...

822
01:01:29.852 --> 01:01:31.520
- Who's that?
- What happened?

823
01:01:32.563 --> 01:01:34.439
They took our guns.

824
01:01:34.606 --> 01:01:36.400
And our uniforms.

825
01:01:42.990 --> 01:01:45.742
And as we recognize
the sacrifice of this man...

826
01:01:45.909 --> 01:01:49.872
...we must remember that vigilance
is the price of safety.

827
01:01:50.038 --> 01:01:52.541
Stand by. Honor guard.

828
01:01:52.708 --> 01:01:56.336
Attention. Port arms.

829
01:01:57.546 --> 01:02:01.925
Ready! Aim! Fire!

830
01:02:02.718 --> 01:02:04.261
Ready! Aim!

831
01:02:07.890 --> 01:02:10.267
Ready! Aim!

832
01:02:18.692 --> 01:02:20.110
Stay down! Don't move!

833
01:02:21.945 --> 01:02:23.614
Mr. Mayor. Get him out of here.

834
01:02:32.831 --> 01:02:35.083
- I'll see you later.
- Why are you going back?

835
01:02:47.721 --> 01:02:48.764
Get out of here.

836
01:02:52.809 --> 01:02:54.561
Tell me what you know about the Joker.

837
01:03:25.592 --> 01:03:26.927
No.

838
01:03:27.344 --> 01:03:28.679
I'm sorry. Barbara.

839
01:03:29.596 --> 01:03:32.850
Jimmy. go play with your sister.
Go ahead. honey.

840
01:03:33.016 --> 01:03:35.269
If there's anything
we can do. anything you need...

841
01:03:35.435 --> 01:03:37.187
...we're here for you.

842
01:03:40.858 --> 01:03:42.109
Are you out there?

843
01:03:43.443 --> 01:03:47.948
Are you? You brought this
craziness on us. You did!

844
01:03:48.115 --> 01:03:50.492
You brought this on us!

845
01:03:51.535 --> 01:03:56.123
Switch it off. he ain't coming.
He doesn't wanna talk to us.

846
01:03:56.540 --> 01:03:59.543
God help whoever
he does wanna talk to.

847
01:04:01.211 --> 01:04:04.131
Can't we go someplace quieter?
We can't hear each other talk.

848
01:04:04.298 --> 01:04:07.134
What makes you think
I wanna hear you talk?

849
01:04:07.301 --> 01:04:08.343
What?

850
01:04:37.748 --> 01:04:39.374
- Yeah?
Second.

851
01:04:39.541 --> 01:04:40.584
Okay.

852
01:04:40.751 --> 01:04:42.920
- Harvey. where are you?
Where are you?

853
01:04:43.086 --> 01:04:45.214
I'm where you should be.
at Major Crimes.

854
01:04:45.380 --> 01:04:46.924
I'm trying to deal with all of this mess.

855
01:04:47.090 --> 01:04:50.677
- Can I get the fingerprint analysis?
- Rachel. listen. You're not safe there.

856
01:04:50.844 --> 01:04:52.638
- This is Gordon's unit.
- Gordon 's gone.

857
01:04:52.804 --> 01:04:56.391
He vouched for these men.
- And he's gone.

858
01:05:01.021 --> 01:05:03.106
The Joker's named you next.

859
01:05:03.273 --> 01:05:06.276
God. is there someone. is there anyone
in this town we can trust?

860
01:05:06.443 --> 01:05:08.153
Bruce.

861
01:05:08.445 --> 01:05:09.613
We can trust Bruce Wayne.

862
01:05:09.780 --> 01:05:11.365
No. Rachel. I know
you're his friend. but...

863
01:05:11.532 --> 01:05:13.367
Harvey. trust me.

864
01:05:13.534 --> 01:05:16.286
Bruce's penthouse is now
the safest place in the city.

865
01:05:16.453 --> 01:05:17.788
Then you go straight there.

866
01:05:17.955 --> 01:05:20.082
Don 't tell anybody
and I'll find you there.

867
01:05:20.249 --> 01:05:21.959
I love you.

868
01:05:35.973 --> 01:05:37.224
I want the Joker.

869
01:05:38.433 --> 01:05:40.102
From one professional to another...

870
01:05:40.269 --> 01:05:42.813
...you're trying to scare somebody.
pick a better spot.

871
01:05:42.980 --> 01:05:45.566
From this height.
the fall wouldn't kill me.

872
01:05:45.732 --> 01:05:47.317
I'm counting on it.

873
01:05:54.700 --> 01:05:57.828
- Where is he?
- I don't know where he is. He found us.

874
01:05:57.995 --> 01:05:59.288
He must have friends.

875
01:05:59.621 --> 01:06:01.915
Friends? Have you met this guy?

876
01:06:02.082 --> 01:06:03.667
Someone knows where he is.

877
01:06:03.834 --> 01:06:06.336
Nobody's gonna tell you nothing.

878
01:06:06.503 --> 01:06:07.838
They're wise to your act.

879
01:06:08.005 --> 01:06:12.009
You got rules.
The Joker. he's got no rules.

880
01:06:12.176 --> 01:06:17.055
Nobody's gonna cross him for you.
If you want this guy. you got one way.

881
01:06:17.222 --> 01:06:19.016
But you already know what that is.

882
01:06:19.183 --> 01:06:21.977
Just take off that mask.
let him come find you.

883
01:06:23.604 --> 01:06:27.691
Or you can let a couple more people
get killed while you make up your mind.

884
01:06:29.359 --> 01:06:31.361
You wanna play games?

885
01:06:37.659 --> 01:06:38.702
How's that feel?

886
01:06:38.869 --> 01:06:41.497
- You wouldn't.
- I wouldn't!

887
01:06:42.998 --> 01:06:44.625
You don't think I will?

888
01:06:44.791 --> 01:06:46.835
You don't think I will?

889
01:06:48.212 --> 01:06:51.423
No. No. I wouldn't.

890
01:06:52.633 --> 01:06:55.177
That's why I'm not
gonna leave it up to me.

891
01:06:56.178 --> 01:06:59.181
Heads. you get to keep your head.

892
01:06:59.598 --> 01:07:01.225
Tails...

893
01:07:02.184 --> 01:07:03.227
...not so lucky.

894
01:07:03.602 --> 01:07:07.147
So you wanna tell me about the Joker?

895
01:07:16.532 --> 01:07:20.244
- Let's go again.
- I don't know anything! God. don't!

896
01:07:20.410 --> 01:07:22.788
You're not playing the odds. friend.

897
01:07:23.914 --> 01:07:25.916
Let's do it again.

898
01:07:28.752 --> 01:07:30.587
You'd leave a man's life to chance?

899
01:07:31.338 --> 01:07:34.925
- Not exactly.
- His name's Schiff. Thomas.

900
01:07:35.092 --> 01:07:38.095
He's a paranoid schizophrenic.
former patient at Arkham.

901
01:07:38.262 --> 01:07:42.891
The kind of mind the Joker attracts.
What do you expect to learn from him?

902
01:07:46.228 --> 01:07:49.022
The Joker killed Gordon.
He's gonna kill Rachel.

903
01:07:49.189 --> 01:07:51.984
You're the symbol of hope
I could never be.

904
01:07:52.150 --> 01:07:53.986
Your stand against organized crime...

905
01:07:54.152 --> 01:07:57.364
...is the first legitimate ray of light
in Gotham in decades.

906
01:07:57.531 --> 01:08:01.159
If anyone saw this.
everything would be undone.

907
01:08:01.326 --> 01:08:03.620
The criminals you arrested
would be released...

908
01:08:03.787 --> 01:08:06.874
...and Jim Gordon
will have died for nothing.

909
01:08:07.499 --> 01:08:09.751
You're gonna hold
a press conference tomorrow.

910
01:08:09.918 --> 01:08:12.296
- Why?
- No one else will die because of me.

911
01:08:12.462 --> 01:08:14.798
Gotham's in your hands now.

912
01:08:14.965 --> 01:08:16.675
You can't.

913
01:08:16.842 --> 01:08:18.218
You can't give in.

914
01:08:18.510 --> 01:08:21.054
You can't give in!

915
01:08:36.403 --> 01:08:37.654
Harvey called.

916
01:08:37.821 --> 01:08:40.866
He said Batman's gonna turn himself in.

917
01:08:41.033 --> 01:08:42.159
I have no choice.

918
01:08:42.326 --> 01:08:45.412
You honestly think that's gonna
keep the Joker from killing people?

919
01:08:45.579 --> 01:08:49.041
Maybe not. But I have enough blood
on my hands.

920
01:08:49.500 --> 01:08:54.338
And I've seen now what I would
have to become to stop men like him.

921
01:08:54.880 --> 01:08:58.342
You once told me that
if the day came when I was finished...

922
01:08:58.509 --> 01:09:00.594
...that we'd be together.

923
01:09:01.303 --> 01:09:04.473
Bruce. don't make me
your one hope for a normal life.

924
01:09:06.016 --> 01:09:07.351
Did you mean it?

925
01:09:08.852 --> 01:09:10.687
Yes.

926
01:09:27.955 --> 01:09:29.748
Bruce.

927
01:09:30.707 --> 01:09:34.628
If you turn yourself in.
they're not gonna let us be together.

928
01:09:45.264 --> 01:09:48.225
Logs as well?
Everything.

929
01:09:48.392 --> 01:09:51.770
Anything that could lead back
to Lucius or Rachel.

930
01:09:57.109 --> 01:10:00.404
People are dying. Alfred.
What would you have me do?

931
01:10:00.571 --> 01:10:04.324
Endure. Master Wayne. Take it.

932
01:10:04.491 --> 01:10:08.203
They'll hate you for it.
but that's the point of Batman.

933
01:10:08.370 --> 01:10:13.917
He can be the outcast. He can make
the choice that no one else can make.

934
01:10:14.084 --> 01:10:15.419
The right choice.

935
01:10:15.919 --> 01:10:18.964
No. today I found out
what Batman can't do.

936
01:10:19.131 --> 01:10:20.382
He can't endure this.

937
01:10:20.674 --> 01:10:23.552
Today you get to say "I told you so."

938
01:10:24.136 --> 01:10:27.306
Today. I don't want to.

939
01:10:33.145 --> 01:10:34.605
But I did bloody tell you.

940
01:10:37.649 --> 01:10:40.652
I suppose they're gonna
lock me up as well...

941
01:10:41.445 --> 01:10:42.696
...as your accomplice.

942
01:10:42.863 --> 01:10:47.618
Accomplice? I'm gonna tell them
the whole thing was your idea.

943
01:10:51.872 --> 01:10:55.417
Ladies and gentlemen. I've called
this press conference for two reasons.

944
01:10:55.584 --> 01:10:57.628
Firstly. to assure the citizens
of Gotham...

945
01:10:57.794 --> 01:11:01.465
...that everything that can be done
over the Joker killings is being done.

946
01:11:02.841 --> 01:11:05.928
Secondly. because the Batman
has offered to turn himself in.

947
01:11:06.094 --> 01:11:07.804
But let's consider the situation.

948
01:11:08.180 --> 01:11:10.807
Should we give in
to this terrorist's demands?

949
01:11:10.974 --> 01:11:12.434
Do we really think he's gonna...?

950
01:11:12.601 --> 01:11:15.979
You'd rather protect an outlaw vigilante
than the lives of citizens?

951
01:11:16.146 --> 01:11:18.524
The Batman is an outlaw.

952
01:11:19.399 --> 01:11:21.318
That's not why we demand
he turn himself in...

953
01:11:21.485 --> 01:11:23.153
...we're doing it because we're scared.

954
01:11:23.320 --> 01:11:26.114
We've been happy to let Batman
clean up our streets till now.

955
01:11:26.281 --> 01:11:29.243
Things are worse than ever!
Amen.

956
01:11:30.577 --> 01:11:32.496
Yes. they are.

957
01:11:34.998 --> 01:11:38.001
But the night is darkest
just before the dawn.

958
01:11:40.462 --> 01:11:42.548
And I promise you...

959
01:11:43.340 --> 01:11:44.758
...the dawn is coming.

960
01:11:44.925 --> 01:11:49.471
One day. the Batman will have to answer
for the laws he's broken. But to us...

961
01:11:49.638 --> 01:11:51.390
...not to this madman.

962
01:11:51.557 --> 01:11:53.892
- No more dead cops!
Yeah!

963
01:11:57.187 --> 01:11:58.772
He should turn himself in!

964
01:11:58.939 --> 01:12:01.650
Give us the Batman! Come on!
Where is he?

965
01:12:04.528 --> 01:12:06.697
So be it. Take the Batman into custody.

966
01:12:07.155 --> 01:12:09.116
What?
Is he here?

967
01:12:09.825 --> 01:12:10.868
I am the Batman.

968
01:12:11.201 --> 01:12:14.204
What?
Come on.

969
01:12:22.588 --> 01:12:24.506
Alfred.

970
01:12:25.841 --> 01:12:27.634
Why is he letting Harvey do this?

971
01:12:27.801 --> 01:12:30.804
- He went down to the press conference.
- I know. He just stood by.

972
01:12:30.971 --> 01:12:33.056
Perhaps both Bruce and Mr. Dent...

973
01:12:33.223 --> 01:12:36.226
...believe that Batman stands for
something more important...

974
01:12:36.393 --> 01:12:38.729
...than the whims of a terrorist.
Miss Dawes...

975
01:12:38.896 --> 01:12:40.898
...even if everyone hates him for it.

976
01:12:41.064 --> 01:12:43.192
That's the sacrifice he's making.

977
01:12:43.358 --> 01:12:46.987
He's not being a hero.
He's being something more.

978
01:12:47.529 --> 01:12:49.156
Yeah. you're absolutely right.

979
01:12:49.323 --> 01:12:52.409
Letting Harvey take the fall for this
is not heroic at all.

980
01:12:55.078 --> 01:12:56.705
You know him better than anyone.

981
01:12:57.122 --> 01:12:58.165
I do.

982
01:13:01.543 --> 01:13:04.588
Will you give this to him for me?
When the time is right?

983
01:13:06.048 --> 01:13:07.257
How will I know?

984
01:13:07.424 --> 01:13:08.926
It's not sealed.

985
01:13:10.344 --> 01:13:11.887
Goodbye. Alfred.

986
01:13:16.058 --> 01:13:17.809
Bye. Rachel.

987
01:13:25.692 --> 01:13:27.528
I didn't have time to talk this through.

988
01:13:27.694 --> 01:13:28.946
What are you doing?

989
01:13:29.112 --> 01:13:31.198
They're transferring me
to Central Holding.

990
01:13:31.490 --> 01:13:35.160
This is the Joker's chance. and when he
attacks. the Batman will take him down.

991
01:13:35.327 --> 01:13:36.870
Listen. This is too dangerous.

992
01:13:37.037 --> 01:13:40.749
We get this guy to County. he's their
problem. The streets will be cleared...

993
01:13:40.916 --> 01:13:44.628
...so let's go.
The convoys stop for no reason.

994
01:13:44.795 --> 01:13:46.255
I hope you got some moves. pal.

995
01:13:46.421 --> 01:13:49.341
He's using you as bait. He doesn't
know if he can get the Joker.

996
01:13:49.508 --> 01:13:50.592
He's failed so far.

997
01:13:50.926 --> 01:13:52.469
How do you know
what he's thinking?

998
01:13:52.636 --> 01:13:54.972
I just do. Anyway.
this isn't just about you.

999
01:13:55.138 --> 01:13:56.974
What about the people
depending on you...

1000
01:13:57.140 --> 01:14:00.143
...to clean the city up
and do it honorably and...?

1001
01:14:05.816 --> 01:14:08.443
Harvey. Tell everyone the truth.

1002
01:14:08.819 --> 01:14:10.696
Heads. I go through with it.

1003
01:14:10.904 --> 01:14:12.823
This is your life. You can't leave...

1004
01:14:12.990 --> 01:14:15.367
...something like that to chance.
- I'm not.

1005
01:14:19.705 --> 01:14:22.124
You make your own luck.

1006
01:14:43.937 --> 01:14:45.939
Hey. you wait like everybody else. pal.

1007
01:14:53.572 --> 01:14:55.908
What the hell is that?

1008
01:14:56.074 --> 01:14:58.285
Obstruction ahead. obstruction ahead!

1009
01:14:58.452 --> 01:15:01.663
Damn it! All units divert down
onto Lower Fifth. I repeat. exit down.

1010
01:15:02.080 --> 01:15:03.207
Exit down!

1011
01:15:03.373 --> 01:15:05.709
Lower Fifth? We'll be
like turkeys on Thanksgiving.

1012
01:15:38.408 --> 01:15:40.744
Jesus. Come on. get us out of here.
Let's go.

1013
01:15:42.913 --> 01:15:45.290
Listen. we need backup.
We've got company.

1014
01:15:45.457 --> 01:15:47.000
We got trouble. guys.

1015
01:15:49.920 --> 01:15:51.004
Lock and load!

1016
01:16:02.224 --> 01:16:03.600
The hell was that?

1017
01:16:25.455 --> 01:16:28.125
- These are built for that. right?
- He'll need something...

1018
01:16:28.292 --> 01:16:30.085
...a lot bigger to get through this.

1019
01:16:31.128 --> 01:16:32.588
What is that?

1020
01:16:33.922 --> 01:16:35.257
What is that. a bazooka?

1021
01:16:43.891 --> 01:16:45.601
I didn't sign up for this!

1022
01:17:01.950 --> 01:17:03.285
Look out.

1023
01:17:04.077 --> 01:17:05.245
Look out!

1024
01:17:27.518 --> 01:17:28.644
Come on. let's go!

1025
01:18:15.232 --> 01:18:17.442
Harvey. Harvey. Harvey Dent.

1026
01:18:17.609 --> 01:18:20.445
Oh. excuse me. I wanna drive.

1027
01:18:25.367 --> 01:18:28.954
Scanning all systems.
Scanning all systems.

1028
01:18:36.420 --> 01:18:38.547
We gotta get topside.
We need air support. now!

1029
01:18:44.052 --> 01:18:45.929
I like this job. I like it.

1030
01:18:48.182 --> 01:18:50.809
Damage catastrophic.
Eject sequence initiated.

1031
01:19:04.781 --> 01:19:06.283
Goodbye.

1032
01:19:15.375 --> 01:19:18.587
We're on point. ready to give them
some of their own medicine.

1033
01:19:24.968 --> 01:19:27.429
That's what I'm talking about. Air cav.

1034
01:19:40.984 --> 01:19:42.694
Okay. rack them up.

1035
01:19:42.861 --> 01:19:45.239
Rack them up. rack them up.
rack them up.

1036
01:20:10.973 --> 01:20:12.140
That's not good.

1037
01:20:15.644 --> 01:20:16.854
Okay. that's not good!

1038
01:20:59.980 --> 01:21:02.065
Now. there's a Batman.

1039
01:21:06.361 --> 01:21:07.571
Ooh. you wanna play. Come on.

1040
01:21:10.491 --> 01:21:11.617
Come on.

1041
01:21:20.751 --> 01:21:22.002
He missed!

1042
01:21:35.933 --> 01:21:38.352
You can't stop here.
We're like sitting ducks!

1043
01:21:55.369 --> 01:21:56.453
Come on. come on.

1044
01:21:59.581 --> 01:22:02.960
Come on. Come on. I want you to do it.
I want you to do it. Come on!

1045
01:22:05.504 --> 01:22:06.964
Come on.

1046
01:22:07.631 --> 01:22:10.968
Come on. I want you to do it.
I want you to do it. Come on. hit me.

1047
01:22:11.134 --> 01:22:12.761
Come on. hit me. Come on. hit me!

1048
01:22:14.888 --> 01:22:15.931
Hit me!

1049
01:22:40.914 --> 01:22:44.168
Come on. come on.

1050
01:22:44.334 --> 01:22:46.587
Could you please just give me a minute?

1051
01:22:48.672 --> 01:22:50.507
We got you. you son of a bitch.

1052
01:22:53.802 --> 01:22:57.723
Gor... You do like to play things
pretty close to the chest.

1053
01:22:58.182 --> 01:22:59.892
We got him. Harvey.

1054
01:23:00.058 --> 01:23:03.520
Mr. Dent! How does it feel
to be the biggest hero in Gotham?

1055
01:23:03.687 --> 01:23:06.982
No. I'm no hero.
Gotham's finest. they're the heroes.

1056
01:23:07.149 --> 01:23:08.483
But you and your office...

1057
01:23:08.650 --> 01:23:10.319
...have been working
with the Batman all along.

1058
01:23:10.485 --> 01:23:12.279
No. but I trusted him
to do the right thing.

1059
01:23:12.446 --> 01:23:14.531
Which was?
- Saving my ass.

1060
01:23:14.698 --> 01:23:17.618
All right. people. that's enough.
Let him be. Let him be.

1061
01:23:17.784 --> 01:23:19.703
Thank you. detective.

1062
01:23:19.912 --> 01:23:22.039
I've got a date
with a pretty upset girlfriend.

1063
01:23:22.206 --> 01:23:24.583
- I figured. counselor.
Mr. Dent. sir...

1064
01:23:24.750 --> 01:23:28.879
...how about one for the front page. sir?
Mr. Dent.

1065
01:23:30.339 --> 01:23:32.341
PEOPLE CHATTERING

1066
01:23:40.224 --> 01:23:43.393
Stand away! All of you!

1067
01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:47.064
I don't want anything for his Mob lawyer
to use. you understand?

1068
01:23:49.316 --> 01:23:51.193
Back from the dead.

1069
01:23:53.570 --> 01:23:55.489
...couldn't risk my family's safety.

1070
01:23:56.782 --> 01:23:58.617
What do we got?

1071
01:24:00.285 --> 01:24:04.248
Nothing. No matches on prints.
DNA. dental.

1072
01:24:04.414 --> 01:24:07.167
Clothing is custom. no labels.

1073
01:24:07.376 --> 01:24:09.503
Nothing in his pockets
but knives and lint.

1074
01:24:09.670 --> 01:24:11.588
No name.

1075
01:24:11.922 --> 01:24:13.882
- No other alias.
Go home. Gordon.

1076
01:24:14.049 --> 01:24:17.135
The clown'll keep till morning.
Go get some rest.

1077
01:24:17.302 --> 01:24:19.137
You're gonna need it.

1078
01:24:19.388 --> 01:24:21.974
Tomorrow you take the big job.

1079
01:24:22.641 --> 01:24:25.811
You don't have any say in the matter.
Commissioner Gordon.

1080
01:24:41.660 --> 01:24:43.787
I'm sorry. I couldn't risk your safety.

1081
01:24:50.294 --> 01:24:51.712
Look at these ugly bastards.

1082
01:24:51.879 --> 01:24:53.755
- I don't feel good.
You're a cop killer.

1083
01:24:53.922 --> 01:24:56.258
You're lucky to be feeling anything
below the neck.

1084
01:24:56.425 --> 01:24:58.010
- Please!
- Step away from the bars!

1085
01:24:58.177 --> 01:25:00.345
My insides hurt.

1086
01:25:14.526 --> 01:25:16.320
Did Batman save you. Daddy?

1087
01:25:18.489 --> 01:25:20.782
Actually. this time...

1088
01:25:20.949 --> 01:25:23.118
...I saved him.

1089
01:25:34.463 --> 01:25:36.089
Has he said anything yet?

1090
01:25:43.680 --> 01:25:47.893
Evening. commissioner.

1091
01:25:55.526 --> 01:25:57.736
Harvey Dent never made it home.

1092
01:25:57.903 --> 01:26:00.030
- Of course not.
- What have you done with him?

1093
01:26:00.948 --> 01:26:02.699
Me?

1094
01:26:04.326 --> 01:26:06.453
I was right here.

1095
01:26:07.871 --> 01:26:09.706
Who did you leave him with?

1096
01:26:09.873 --> 01:26:12.709
Hm? Your people?

1097
01:26:13.836 --> 01:26:17.172
Assuming. of course.
that they are still your people...

1098
01:26:17.339 --> 01:26:20.050
...and not Maroni's.

1099
01:26:22.261 --> 01:26:24.638
Does it depress you. commissioner...

1100
01:26:25.055 --> 01:26:30.018
...to know just how alone you really are?

1101
01:26:32.020 --> 01:26:36.900
Does it make you feel responsible
for Harvey Dent's current predicament?

1102
01:26:37.067 --> 01:26:39.736
- Where is he?
- What's the time?

1103
01:26:40.237 --> 01:26:41.738
What difference does that make?

1104
01:26:41.989 --> 01:26:47.452
Well. depending on the time.
he may be in one spot or several.

1105
01:26:53.834 --> 01:26:56.795
If we're gonna play games...

1106
01:26:59.965 --> 01:27:01.925
...I'm gonna need a cup of coffee.

1107
01:27:02.092 --> 01:27:06.180
Ah. the "good cop. bad cop" routine?

1108
01:27:06.847 --> 01:27:07.890
Not exactly.

1109
01:27:18.400 --> 01:27:22.446
Never start with the head. The victim
gets all fuzzy. He can't feel the next...

1110
01:27:25.616 --> 01:27:26.742
See?

1111
01:27:26.909 --> 01:27:29.244
You wanted me. Here I am.

1112
01:27:30.287 --> 01:27:32.414
I wanted to see what you'd do.

1113
01:27:32.956 --> 01:27:35.542
And you didn't disappoint.

1114
01:27:35.709 --> 01:27:38.545
You let five people die.

1115
01:27:39.505 --> 01:27:43.175
Then you let Dent take your place.

1116
01:27:43.342 --> 01:27:45.969
- Even to a guy like me. that's cold.
- Where's Dent?

1117
01:27:46.136 --> 01:27:50.933
Those Mob fools want you gone so they
can get back to the way things were.

1118
01:27:51.433 --> 01:27:56.188
But I know the truth. There's no
going back. You've changed things.

1119
01:27:56.355 --> 01:27:58.774
- Forever.
- Then why do you wanna kill me?

1120
01:28:01.735 --> 01:28:03.153
I don't wanna kill you.

1121
01:28:03.654 --> 01:28:08.200
What would I do without you? Go back
to ripping off Mob dealers? No. no.

1122
01:28:08.367 --> 01:28:10.744
No. No. you...

1123
01:28:10.911 --> 01:28:13.330
You complete me.

1124
01:28:13.497 --> 01:28:17.835
- You're garbage who kills for money.
- Don't talk like one of them. You're not.

1125
01:28:18.001 --> 01:28:20.420
Even if you'd like to be.

1126
01:28:21.672 --> 01:28:23.507
To them. you're just a freak...

1127
01:28:24.424 --> 01:28:25.759
...like me.

1128
01:28:25.926 --> 01:28:28.220
They need you right now...

1129
01:28:28.804 --> 01:28:30.848
...but when they don't...

1130
01:28:31.390 --> 01:28:34.434
...they'll cast you out like a leper.

1131
01:28:34.601 --> 01:28:38.522
You see. their morals. their code...

1132
01:28:38.772 --> 01:28:40.941
...it's a bad joke.

1133
01:28:41.191 --> 01:28:44.528
Dropped at the first sign of trouble.

1134
01:28:45.195 --> 01:28:49.199
They're only as good as the world
allows them to be. I'll show you.

1135
01:28:49.366 --> 01:28:52.536
When the chips are down. these...

1136
01:28:52.703 --> 01:28:54.955
These civilized people...

1137
01:28:55.122 --> 01:28:57.207
...they'll eat each other.

1138
01:28:57.916 --> 01:29:00.294
See. I'm not a monster.

1139
01:29:01.670 --> 01:29:02.963
I'm just ahead of the curve.

1140
01:29:05.215 --> 01:29:06.300
Where's Dent?

1141
01:29:06.466 --> 01:29:09.386
You have all these rules.
and you think they'll save you.

1142
01:29:12.472 --> 01:29:14.892
- He's in control.
- I have one rule.

1143
01:29:15.058 --> 01:29:18.145
Oh. Then that's the rule you'll have
to break to know the truth.

1144
01:29:18.312 --> 01:29:19.479
Which is?

1145
01:29:19.646 --> 01:29:22.065
The only sensible way to live
is without rules.

1146
01:29:22.232 --> 01:29:24.902
And tonight you're gonna break
your one rule.

1147
01:29:25.068 --> 01:29:26.111
I'm considering it.

1148
01:29:26.278 --> 01:29:28.906
There's only minutes left.
so you'll have to play my game...

1149
01:29:29.072 --> 01:29:31.658
...if you wanna save one of them.

1150
01:29:32.159 --> 01:29:33.202
"Them"?

1151
01:29:33.368 --> 01:29:37.414
You know. for a while there.
I thought you really were Dent.

1152
01:29:37.581 --> 01:29:40.209
The way you threw yourself after her.

1153
01:29:46.507 --> 01:29:47.591
Look at you go.

1154
01:29:53.222 --> 01:29:56.808
Does Harvey know
about you and his little bunny?

1155
01:29:57.726 --> 01:29:59.102
Where are they?!

1156
01:29:59.269 --> 01:30:01.271
Killing is making a choice.

1157
01:30:01.438 --> 01:30:04.525
- Where are they?!
- Choose between one life or the other.

1158
01:30:05.275 --> 01:30:09.530
Your friend the district attorney.
or his blushing bride-to-be.

1159
01:30:14.701 --> 01:30:18.789
You have nothing.
nothing to threaten me with.

1160
01:30:19.206 --> 01:30:22.709
Nothing to do with all your strength.

1161
01:30:22.918 --> 01:30:26.338
Don't worry. I'm gonna tell you
where they are. both of them.

1162
01:30:26.505 --> 01:30:29.550
And that's the point.
You'll have to choose.

1163
01:30:30.300 --> 01:30:33.136
He's at 25052nd Street...

1164
01:30:33.303 --> 01:30:36.640
...and she's on Avenue X at Cicero.

1165
01:30:38.725 --> 01:30:40.477
- Which one you going after?
- Rachel.

1166
01:30:41.895 --> 01:30:43.313
We're getting Dent!

1167
01:30:45.566 --> 01:30:48.402
250 52nd Street!

1168
01:30:51.321 --> 01:30:53.157
Hello?

1169
01:30:54.116 --> 01:30:56.493
Can anybody hear me?

1170
01:30:58.912 --> 01:31:01.540
Hello!

1171
01:31:05.544 --> 01:31:07.796
- Rachel?
- Harvey.

1172
01:31:07.963 --> 01:31:10.174
Oh. Harvey. thank God. Are you okay?

1173
01:31:10.340 --> 01:31:11.925
I'm all right. I'm in a...

1174
01:31:12.092 --> 01:31:15.679
I'm in a warehouse.
They got me wired to these oil drums.

1175
01:31:16.722 --> 01:31:17.931
I am too.

1176
01:31:18.473 --> 01:31:20.184
Harvey.

1177
01:31:27.441 --> 01:31:29.902
I want my phone call.

1178
01:31:30.068 --> 01:31:32.863
I want it. I want it.
I want my phone call.

1179
01:31:33.530 --> 01:31:35.365
That's nice.

1180
01:31:36.867 --> 01:31:41.705
How many of your friends have I killed?

1181
01:31:45.459 --> 01:31:46.543
I'm a 20-year man...

1182
01:31:46.710 --> 01:31:50.172
...and I know the difference between
punks who need a lesson in manners...

1183
01:31:50.339 --> 01:31:53.217
...and the freaks like you
who would just enjoy it.

1184
01:31:54.092 --> 01:31:56.553
And you killed six of my friends.

1185
01:31:57.930 --> 01:32:00.390
Please. My insides hurt.

1186
01:32:00.557 --> 01:32:02.309
I don't really care. Back away.

1187
01:32:02.476 --> 01:32:05.646
The boss said he'd make the voices
go away.

1188
01:32:05.812 --> 01:32:09.358
He said he'd go inside
and replace them with bright lights...

1189
01:32:09.525 --> 01:32:10.651
...like Christmas.

1190
01:32:10.817 --> 01:32:13.362
You're out of your mind. pal. Back off.

1191
01:32:13.529 --> 01:32:16.365
Medic to the holding tank.
Come on. Get the door open.

1192
01:32:16.573 --> 01:32:17.741
You guys. back off!

1193
01:32:17.908 --> 01:32:20.077
Listen. we don't have a lot of time.

1194
01:32:20.244 --> 01:32:24.248
They told me that only one of us
was gonna make it...

1195
01:32:24.414 --> 01:32:27.751
...and that they were gonna
let our friends choose.

1196
01:32:30.462 --> 01:32:32.589
Okay. Rachel.

1197
01:32:33.173 --> 01:32:36.301
It's gonna be fine. It's gonna be all right.
They're coming for you.

1198
01:32:36.468 --> 01:32:40.764
Listen to me. I'll help you. Just talk me
through what's going on with you.

1199
01:32:40.931 --> 01:32:42.850
Can you find something.
anything. sharp?

1200
01:32:43.016 --> 01:32:44.434
I'm trying.

1201
01:32:44.601 --> 01:32:46.770
- What's...?
- Shit.

1202
01:32:46.937 --> 01:32:48.438
Harvey?

1203
01:32:52.192 --> 01:32:53.861
Harvey. what's happening?

1204
01:33:03.203 --> 01:33:07.040
All available units.
converge at 250 52nd Street.

1205
01:33:07.374 --> 01:33:11.461
Do you wanna know why I use a knife?

1206
01:33:13.755 --> 01:33:15.090
Guns are too quick.

1207
01:33:15.257 --> 01:33:18.635
You can't savor all the...

1208
01:33:18.802 --> 01:33:22.139
...little emotions.

1209
01:33:24.057 --> 01:33:28.937
You see. in their last moments...

1210
01:33:29.104 --> 01:33:31.398
...people show you who they really are.

1211
01:33:32.482 --> 01:33:38.155
So in a way. I knew your friends
better than you ever did.

1212
01:33:41.909 --> 01:33:45.329
Would you like to know
which of them were cowards?

1213
01:33:51.835 --> 01:33:53.504
What's that?
Jeez.

1214
01:33:53.712 --> 01:33:55.756
He's got some kind of a...

1215
01:33:55.923 --> 01:33:59.134
...contusion.
- I know you're gonna enjoy this.

1216
01:34:00.511 --> 01:34:04.264
I'm gonna have to try and enjoy it
even more.

1217
01:34:11.813 --> 01:34:12.856
Just put it down.

1218
01:34:13.023 --> 01:34:15.817
Take it easy. Take it easy.
Drop the weapon now!

1219
01:34:15.984 --> 01:34:19.947
- It's my own damn fault. just shoot him!
- Let him go now! Drop it!

1220
01:34:20.239 --> 01:34:23.242
- What? Sorry?
- What do you want?

1221
01:34:24.284 --> 01:34:26.203
I just want my phone call.

1222
01:34:29.206 --> 01:34:31.875
What...? What...? What's happening?

1223
01:34:32.042 --> 01:34:34.878
Just talk to me. just for one second.

1224
01:34:37.214 --> 01:34:39.883
- All right?
- Right.

1225
01:34:51.687 --> 01:34:53.730
Is that a phone?

1226
01:35:03.407 --> 01:35:04.741
Mount the curb!

1227
01:35:12.749 --> 01:35:16.753
Harvey. just in case.
I wanna tell you something. okay?

1228
01:35:16.920 --> 01:35:18.714
Don't think like that. They're coming.

1229
01:35:18.881 --> 01:35:21.175
I know they are.
but I don't want them to.

1230
01:35:25.596 --> 01:35:29.683
I don't wanna live without you.
and I do have an answer for you.

1231
01:35:30.100 --> 01:35:31.852
My answer is yes.

1232
01:35:34.605 --> 01:35:37.357
No! No! No!

1233
01:35:37.524 --> 01:35:40.152
Not me! Why are you coming for me?

1234
01:35:40.319 --> 01:35:41.361
No!

1235
01:35:43.030 --> 01:35:44.615
Rachel! Rachel!

1236
01:35:44.823 --> 01:35:47.159
- Harvey.
- No! No! Rachel!

1237
01:35:47.326 --> 01:35:48.368
Okay.

1238
01:35:51.747 --> 01:35:55.876
Harvey. it's okay. It's all right. Listen.

1239
01:35:56.043 --> 01:35:57.377
Somewh...

1240
01:36:03.258 --> 01:36:04.468
No. commissioner!

1241
01:36:04.635 --> 01:36:07.304
Rachel! No!

1242
01:36:21.652 --> 01:36:22.778
Hello there.

1243
01:36:28.659 --> 01:36:32.162
Back at the MCU. the Joker's gone.

1244
01:36:33.080 --> 01:36:34.790
With Lau?

1245
01:36:37.584 --> 01:36:40.170
The Joker planned to be caught.

1246
01:36:40.504 --> 01:36:42.673
He wanted me to lock him up
in the MCU.

1247
01:37:02.317 --> 01:37:04.361
Dear Bruce:

1248
01:37:06.113 --> 01:37:08.657
I need to be honest and clear.

1249
01:37:10.701 --> 01:37:13.245
I'm going to marry Harvey Dent.

1250
01:37:13.412 --> 01:37:17.332
I love him. and I wanna spend
the rest of my life with him.

1251
01:37:17.875 --> 01:37:22.296
When I told you that if Gotham no longer
needed Batman. we could be together...

1252
01:37:22.462 --> 01:37:24.673
...I meant it.

1253
01:37:24.923 --> 01:37:29.678
But now I'm sure the day won 't come
when you no longer need Batman.

1254
01:37:30.721 --> 01:37:32.639
I hope it does.

1255
01:37:32.806 --> 01:37:35.559
And if it does. I will be there...

1256
01:37:36.101 --> 01:37:37.519
...but as your friend.

1257
01:37:38.228 --> 01:37:40.480
I'm sorry. Harvey.

1258
01:37:40.647 --> 01:37:43.025
I'm sorry to let you down.

1259
01:37:43.192 --> 01:37:48.197
If you lose your faith in me.
please keep your faith in people.

1260
01:37:48.780 --> 01:37:53.202
Love. now and always. Rachel.

1261
01:38:01.168 --> 01:38:03.504
Prepared a little breakfast.

1262
01:38:07.633 --> 01:38:09.551
- Very well. then.
- Alfred.

1263
01:38:09.718 --> 01:38:10.886
Yes. Master Wayne?

1264
01:38:12.262 --> 01:38:14.515
Did I bring this on her?

1265
01:38:15.557 --> 01:38:17.768
I was meant to inspire good...

1266
01:38:17.935 --> 01:38:20.312
...not madness. not death.

1267
01:38:20.479 --> 01:38:25.108
You have inspired good. But you spat
in the faces of Gotham's criminals.

1268
01:38:25.275 --> 01:38:27.361
Didn't you think
there might be casualties?

1269
01:38:27.528 --> 01:38:29.947
Things always get worse
before they get better.

1270
01:38:30.280 --> 01:38:31.740
But Rachel. Alfred.

1271
01:38:31.907 --> 01:38:35.702
Rachel believed in what you stood for...

1272
01:38:35.869 --> 01:38:37.788
...what we stand for.

1273
01:38:37.955 --> 01:38:39.414
Gotham needs you.

1274
01:38:39.957 --> 01:38:42.918
No. Gotham needs its true hero...

1275
01:38:43.418 --> 01:38:47.548
...and I let that murdering psychopath
blow him half to hell.

1276
01:38:47.714 --> 01:38:50.050
Which is why. for now...

1277
01:38:50.843 --> 01:38:52.761
...they're gonna have to
make do with you.

1278
01:38:54.972 --> 01:38:56.807
She was gonna wait for me. Alfred.

1279
01:38:58.809 --> 01:39:00.853
Dent doesn't know.

1280
01:39:01.019 --> 01:39:02.312
He can never know.

1281
01:39:04.731 --> 01:39:06.358
What's that?

1282
01:39:06.525 --> 01:39:09.486
- It can wait.
- That bandit...

1283
01:39:09.945 --> 01:39:12.072
...in the forest in Burma.

1284
01:39:12.239 --> 01:39:14.283
- Did you catch him?
- Yes.

1285
01:39:14.449 --> 01:39:15.784
How?

1286
01:39:17.202 --> 01:39:18.829
We burned the forest down.

1287
01:39:58.076 --> 01:40:00.704
He's credible. an M & A lawyer
from a leading consultancy.

1288
01:40:00.871 --> 01:40:04.249
He says he's waited as long as he can
for Batman to do the right thing.

1289
01:40:04.416 --> 01:40:06.502
Now he's taking matters
into his own hands.

1290
01:40:06.668 --> 01:40:09.630
We'll be live at 5 with
the true identity of the Batman.

1291
01:40:26.063 --> 01:40:27.689
I'm sorry about Rachel.

1292
01:40:30.400 --> 01:40:35.239
The doctor says you're in agonizing pain.
but that you won't accept medication.

1293
01:40:36.281 --> 01:40:38.242
That you're refusing to...

1294
01:40:38.408 --> 01:40:40.160
...accept skin grafts.

1295
01:40:40.494 --> 01:40:42.746
Remember that name...

1296
01:40:43.330 --> 01:40:45.666
...you all had for me...

1297
01:40:46.124 --> 01:40:48.961
...when I was at Internal Affairs?

1298
01:40:51.421 --> 01:40:52.714
What was it. Gordon?

1299
01:40:53.382 --> 01:40:54.758
Harvey. I...

1300
01:40:54.925 --> 01:40:56.426
Say it.

1301
01:40:57.845 --> 01:40:59.763
Say it!

1302
01:41:07.437 --> 01:41:10.524
Two-Face. Harvey Two-Face.

1303
01:41:12.109 --> 01:41:16.405
Why should I hide who I am?

1304
01:41:17.614 --> 01:41:18.949
I know you tried to warn me.

1305
01:41:19.825 --> 01:41:21.034
I'm sorry.

1306
01:41:21.660 --> 01:41:24.288
Wuertz picked you up.
Was he working for them?

1307
01:41:26.582 --> 01:41:28.959
Do you know who picked up Rachel?

1308
01:41:29.793 --> 01:41:32.796
Harvey. I need to know
which of my men I can trust.

1309
01:41:33.172 --> 01:41:35.299
Why would you listen to me now?

1310
01:41:36.425 --> 01:41:38.093
I'm sorry. Harvey.

1311
01:41:40.637 --> 01:41:42.431
No.

1312
01:41:42.890 --> 01:41:45.017
No. you're not.

1313
01:41:46.059 --> 01:41:47.311
Not yet.

1314
01:41:52.566 --> 01:41:55.277
This craziness. it's too much.

1315
01:41:55.486 --> 01:41:58.739
Should've thought about that
before you let the clown out of the box.

1316
01:41:58.906 --> 01:42:00.657
You want him?

1317
01:42:03.118 --> 01:42:05.454
I can tell you
where he'll be this afternoon.

1318
01:42:13.504 --> 01:42:15.797
Not so crazy as you look.

1319
01:42:15.964 --> 01:42:19.718
I told you. I'm a man of my word.

1320
01:42:22.930 --> 01:42:24.181
Where is the Italian?

1321
01:42:24.348 --> 01:42:27.476
All tactical units will converge
on the location in 20 minutes.

1322
01:42:27.643 --> 01:42:31.104
I want auxiliary units to cover
all possible getaway routes.

1323
01:42:31.688 --> 01:42:32.856
Please.

1324
01:42:33.023 --> 01:42:36.360
Joker-man. what you do
with all your money?

1325
01:42:37.027 --> 01:42:39.696
You see. I'm a guy of simple taste.

1326
01:42:39.863 --> 01:42:41.532
I enjoy...

1327
01:42:41.698 --> 01:42:43.075
...dynamite...

1328
01:42:43.242 --> 01:42:44.785
...and gunpowder...

1329
01:42:45.244 --> 01:42:47.663
...and gasoline.

1330
01:42:49.122 --> 01:42:51.375
What the...?

1331
01:42:53.210 --> 01:42:56.046
And you know the thing
that they have in common?

1332
01:42:56.547 --> 01:42:57.840
They're cheap.

1333
01:42:58.006 --> 01:43:00.676
How much are they
paying you to say who Batman is?

1334
01:43:00.843 --> 01:43:04.805
This is our chance. I want Lau alive.
The Joker. either way.

1335
01:43:04.972 --> 01:43:06.390
Hey. Jim. Get a load of this.

1336
01:43:06.557 --> 01:43:07.891
Let's take the next caller.

1337
01:43:08.058 --> 01:43:10.227
Harvey Dent didn 't wanna
give in to this maniac.

1338
01:43:10.394 --> 01:43:11.687
You think you know better?

1339
01:43:11.854 --> 01:43:15.232
I think that if we could talk to Dent
today. he may feel differently.

1340
01:43:15.399 --> 01:43:19.486
And we wish him a speedy recovery.
Because God knows. we need him now.

1341
01:43:19.653 --> 01:43:21.864
You said you were a man of your word.

1342
01:43:22.156 --> 01:43:24.199
Oh. I am.

1343
01:43:25.909 --> 01:43:28.579
I'm only burning my half.

1344
01:43:29.913 --> 01:43:32.040
All you care about is money.

1345
01:43:32.207 --> 01:43:35.669
This town deserves
a better class of criminal...

1346
01:43:35.836 --> 01:43:38.088
...and I'm gonna give it to them.

1347
01:43:38.881 --> 01:43:41.383
Tell your men they work for me now.

1348
01:43:41.550 --> 01:43:43.927
This is my city.

1349
01:43:44.595 --> 01:43:47.139
They won't work for a freak.

1350
01:43:47.306 --> 01:43:49.016
"Freak."

1351
01:43:49.183 --> 01:43:51.643
Why don't we
cut you up into little pieces...

1352
01:43:51.810 --> 01:43:53.270
...and feed you to your pooches? Hm?

1353
01:43:53.437 --> 01:43:56.315
And then we'll see how loyal
a hungry dog really is.

1354
01:43:58.317 --> 01:44:00.652
It's not about money...

1355
01:44:00.819 --> 01:44:04.031
...it's about sending a message.

1356
01:44:04.823 --> 01:44:07.284
Everything burns.

1357
01:44:09.786 --> 01:44:11.955
- Who is this?
I had a vision...

1358
01:44:12.122 --> 01:44:14.875
...of a world without Batman.

1359
01:44:15.042 --> 01:44:17.294
The Mob ground out a little profit...

1360
01:44:17.461 --> 01:44:21.381
...and the police tried to shut them down
one block at a time.

1361
01:44:21.548 --> 01:44:24.843
And it was so boring.

1362
01:44:25.010 --> 01:44:26.970
I've had a change of heart.

1363
01:44:27.137 --> 01:44:29.765
I don 't want Mr. Reese
spoiling everything...

1364
01:44:29.932 --> 01:44:34.645
...but why should I have all the fun?
Let's give someone else a chance.

1365
01:44:34.811 --> 01:44:39.650
If Coleman Reese
isn 't dead in 60 minutes...

1366
01:44:39.817 --> 01:44:41.902
...then I blow up a hospital.

1367
01:44:42.069 --> 01:44:43.654
Call in every officer.

1368
01:44:43.821 --> 01:44:47.157
Tell them to head to their nearest
hospital and start evac and search.

1369
01:44:47.324 --> 01:44:49.451
Call the transit authority.
school board. prisons.

1370
01:44:49.618 --> 01:44:51.245
Get every bus down to a hospital.

1371
01:44:51.411 --> 01:44:55.999
The priority is Gotham General. Wheel
everybody out of that place right now.

1372
01:44:56.166 --> 01:44:57.835
You. you and you. you come with me.

1373
01:44:58.001 --> 01:44:59.878
- Where are we going. sir?
- To get Reese.

1374
01:45:00.212 --> 01:45:03.298
I need you plugged in. checking
Gordon's men and their families.

1375
01:45:03.465 --> 01:45:05.676
- Looking for?
- Hospital admissions.

1376
01:45:05.843 --> 01:45:07.511
Will you be wanting the Batpod?

1377
01:45:07.678 --> 01:45:09.638
In the middle of the day?
Not very subtle.

1378
01:45:09.805 --> 01:45:11.098
The Lamborghini. then.

1379
01:45:12.015 --> 01:45:13.141
Much more subtle.

1380
01:45:26.989 --> 01:45:29.491
Excuse me. Let me through.
Excuse me. Okay.

1381
01:45:29.658 --> 01:45:33.162
Sir. could you help. please?

1382
01:45:33.328 --> 01:45:35.038
I'm gonna find a bus for him.

1383
01:45:36.999 --> 01:45:38.876
Sir? Commissioner. do you really think...

1384
01:45:39.042 --> 01:45:41.211
...an ordinary citizen
would try to kill this man?

1385
01:45:45.716 --> 01:45:48.051
Sir. Commissioner.

1386
01:45:50.137 --> 01:45:52.347
Get the cars around the back!

1387
01:45:54.725 --> 01:45:56.059
Go. Keep rolling. Sam.

1388
01:46:02.024 --> 01:46:03.984
I see O'Brien and Richards.

1389
01:46:04.568 --> 01:46:08.071
No immediate family member
admitted to a Gotham hospital.

1390
01:46:09.364 --> 01:46:12.910
They're trying to kill me.
- Well. maybe Batman can save you.

1391
01:46:26.048 --> 01:46:28.675
Davis. they got space. Bring him out.

1392
01:46:30.344 --> 01:46:32.137
Davis.

1393
01:46:37.267 --> 01:46:39.603
I saw Burns and Zachary.

1394
01:46:39.770 --> 01:46:40.979
Nothing on them.

1395
01:46:41.146 --> 01:46:42.606
And a patrolman I don't know.

1396
01:46:43.816 --> 01:46:45.734
Okay. so. what now?

1397
01:46:46.610 --> 01:46:48.862
What do we do now?
Where are we going?

1398
01:46:51.615 --> 01:46:53.283
Send the information to Gordon.

1399
01:47:01.166 --> 01:47:02.709
Get out of here.

1400
01:47:04.753 --> 01:47:06.547
Davis.

1401
01:47:09.716 --> 01:47:12.135
Ma'am. we're gonna have to
move him now.

1402
01:47:23.814 --> 01:47:26.150
It's Berg. isn't it?
- Commissioner.

1403
01:47:27.276 --> 01:47:28.735
You okay. son?

1404
01:47:46.753 --> 01:47:48.338
Hi.

1405
01:47:53.177 --> 01:47:54.678
You know...

1406
01:47:55.512 --> 01:47:58.599
...I don't want there to be
any hard feelings between us. Harvey.

1407
01:47:58.765 --> 01:48:01.894
- When you and...
- Rachel!

1408
01:48:02.060 --> 01:48:04.354
Rachel were being abducted...

1409
01:48:04.521 --> 01:48:07.524
...I was sitting in Gordon's cage.

1410
01:48:07.858 --> 01:48:09.776
I didn't rig those charges.

1411
01:48:09.985 --> 01:48:12.446
Your men. your plan.

1412
01:48:12.654 --> 01:48:15.115
Do I really look like a guy with a plan?

1413
01:48:15.532 --> 01:48:18.327
You know what I am?
I'm a dog chasing cars.

1414
01:48:18.952 --> 01:48:21.413
I wouldn't know what to do with one
if I caught it.

1415
01:48:21.580 --> 01:48:24.708
You know? I just do things.

1416
01:48:25.083 --> 01:48:28.795
The Mob has plans. The cops have plans.

1417
01:48:28.962 --> 01:48:31.173
Gordon's got plans.

1418
01:48:31.340 --> 01:48:34.301
You know. they're schemers.

1419
01:48:34.468 --> 01:48:38.222
Schemers trying to control
their little worlds.

1420
01:48:38.388 --> 01:48:39.890
I'm not a schemer.

1421
01:48:40.057 --> 01:48:41.683
I try to show the schemers...

1422
01:48:41.850 --> 01:48:47.147
...how pathetic their attempts
to control things really are.

1423
01:48:48.106 --> 01:48:51.151
So when I say... Ah. Come here.

1424
01:48:51.652 --> 01:48:55.197
When I say that you and your girlfriend
was nothing personal...

1425
01:48:56.740 --> 01:48:58.951
...you'll know that I'm telling the truth.

1426
01:49:01.453 --> 01:49:04.248
- I'm gonna need your weapon.
- What?

1427
01:49:08.001 --> 01:49:09.837
Why? Because my wife's in the hospital?

1428
01:49:10.546 --> 01:49:12.089
Yeah. that'd be why.

1429
01:49:13.006 --> 01:49:16.218
It's the schemers
that put you where you are.

1430
01:49:16.385 --> 01:49:20.180
You were a schemer. you had plans...

1431
01:49:20.347 --> 01:49:22.516
...and look where that got you.

1432
01:49:33.277 --> 01:49:35.654
Police are taking every precaution...

1433
01:49:35.821 --> 01:49:37.948
...urging people not to
take matters into their hands.

1434
01:49:38.115 --> 01:49:40.659
I just did what I do best.

1435
01:49:40.826 --> 01:49:44.454
I took your little plan
and I turned it on itself.

1436
01:49:44.621 --> 01:49:49.960
Look what I did to this city with a few
drums of gas and a couple of bullets.

1437
01:49:50.127 --> 01:49:53.422
Hm? You know what I noticed?

1438
01:49:53.589 --> 01:49:57.134
Nobody panics when
things go "according to plan."

1439
01:49:57.301 --> 01:49:58.969
Even if the plan is horrifying.

1440
01:49:59.595 --> 01:50:04.641
If tomorrow I tell the press that. like.
a gangbanger will get shot...

1441
01:50:04.808 --> 01:50:08.270
...or a truckload of soldiers
will be blowing up...

1442
01:50:08.562 --> 01:50:09.646
...nobody panics.

1443
01:50:10.355 --> 01:50:13.442
Because it's all part of the plan.

1444
01:50:13.609 --> 01:50:18.530
But when I say that
one little old mayor will die...

1445
01:50:18.780 --> 01:50:21.200
...well. then. everyone loses their minds.

1446
01:50:24.620 --> 01:50:27.539
Introduce a little anarchy...

1447
01:50:28.707 --> 01:50:30.959
...upset the established order...

1448
01:50:31.126 --> 01:50:35.672
...and everything becomes chaos.

1449
01:50:37.508 --> 01:50:40.260
I'm an agent of chaos.

1450
01:50:40.636 --> 01:50:42.971
Oh. and you know the thing
about chaos?

1451
01:50:45.015 --> 01:50:46.642
It's fair.

1452
01:50:55.859 --> 01:50:59.029
You live.

1453
01:50:59.530 --> 01:51:01.156
You die.

1454
01:51:01.365 --> 01:51:03.367
Mmm. Now we're talking.

1455
01:51:12.709 --> 01:51:14.211
Mr. Reese.

1456
01:51:32.396 --> 01:51:34.565
That's Mr. Wayne. isn't it?

1457
01:51:34.731 --> 01:51:37.734
- That was a very brave thing you did.
- Trying to catch the light?

1458
01:51:38.068 --> 01:51:40.904
- You weren't protecting the van?
- Why? Who's in it?

1459
01:51:46.368 --> 01:51:48.453
Don't you think
I should go to the hospital?

1460
01:51:48.620 --> 01:51:51.123
Don't watch a whole lot of news.
do you. Mr. Wayne?

1461
01:52:57.272 --> 01:52:59.107
Southeast.

1462
01:52:59.274 --> 01:53:01.485
It's Gotham General.

1463
01:53:02.236 --> 01:53:03.904
- Did you clear the building?
Yeah.

1464
01:53:06.907 --> 01:53:08.617
You must know
how many were inside.

1465
01:53:08.784 --> 01:53:10.160
You have patient lists. roll call.

1466
01:53:10.327 --> 01:53:12.663
Right now we're showing
50 people missing. One bus.

1467
01:53:12.830 --> 01:53:15.999
The other buses were heading off to
hospitals. I guess we missed one.

1468
01:53:16.166 --> 01:53:18.293
What's your guess
about where Harvey Dent is?

1469
01:53:18.460 --> 01:53:22.923
Keep looking. And keep it to yourself.
Anybody asks. we got him out.

1470
01:53:25.509 --> 01:53:27.928
Get me the mayor's office on the line.

1471
01:53:29.096 --> 01:53:30.848
We're gonna need the National Guard.

1472
01:53:31.014 --> 01:53:32.641
People are still missing...

1473
01:53:32.808 --> 01:53:34.017
...including GCN's own Mike Engel.

1474
01:53:34.184 --> 01:53:37.437
I'm now being told that we're cutting to
a video GCN has just received.

1475
01:53:37.604 --> 01:53:39.523
I'm Mike Engel for Gotham Tonight.

1476
01:53:40.023 --> 01:53:43.360
"What does it take
to make you people wanna join in?

1477
01:53:43.527 --> 01:53:46.113
You failed to kill the lawyer.
I've gotta get you off the bench...

1478
01:53:46.280 --> 01:53:48.031
...and into the game.
Bench. Game.

1479
01:53:48.198 --> 01:53:49.992
JOKER LAUGHS

1480
01:53:50.200 --> 01:53:52.327
Come nightfall. this city is mine.
Mine.

1481
01:53:52.494 --> 01:53:55.247
- And anyone left here plays by my rules.
- Rules.

1482
01:53:55.539 --> 01:53:58.876
Mr. Fox? Security is showing
a break-in at the R & D Department.

1483
01:53:59.042 --> 01:54:01.170
If you don 't wanna be in the game...

1484
01:54:01.336 --> 01:54:02.713
...get out now.
- Get out now.

1485
01:54:04.882 --> 01:54:07.843
But the bridge-and-tunnel crowd
are sure in for a surprise.

1486
01:54:43.587 --> 01:54:44.880
Gotham P.D.
Has shut down...

1487
01:54:45.047 --> 01:54:47.508
Sweet Jesus.
...the area 's bridges and tunnels.

1488
01:54:47.674 --> 01:54:51.094
Shouldn't you be out there.
you know. doing something?

1489
01:54:51.261 --> 01:54:53.222
It's my day off.

1490
01:54:53.847 --> 01:54:55.432
I gotta take a leak.

1491
01:54:55.599 --> 01:54:57.935
Keep an eye out for me. will you?

1492
01:55:03.524 --> 01:55:05.484
Now what?
Need someone to shake it for you?

1493
01:55:05.651 --> 01:55:07.236
Hello.

1494
01:55:07.945 --> 01:55:09.446
Dent.

1495
01:55:09.613 --> 01:55:11.824
Jesus. I thought you was dead.

1496
01:55:11.990 --> 01:55:13.659
Half.

1497
01:55:19.706 --> 01:55:21.291
Who picked up Rachel. Wuertz?

1498
01:55:21.458 --> 01:55:23.460
- It must've been Maroni's men.
- Shut up!

1499
01:55:25.212 --> 01:55:27.339
Are you telling me
that you're gonna protect...

1500
01:55:27.506 --> 01:55:29.258
...the other traitor in Gordon's unit?

1501
01:55:29.424 --> 01:55:30.884
I don't know. he never told me.

1502
01:55:31.051 --> 01:55:34.680
Listen. Dent. I swear to God. I didn't
know what they were gonna do to you.

1503
01:55:36.223 --> 01:55:37.391
That's funny...

1504
01:55:39.143 --> 01:55:41.895
...because I don't know
what's gonna happen to you either.

1505
01:55:44.815 --> 01:55:45.858
GUNSHOT

1506
01:55:46.024 --> 01:55:47.943
Beautiful. isn't it?

1507
01:55:48.318 --> 01:55:49.987
Beautiful.

1508
01:55:50.529 --> 01:55:51.655
Unethical.

1509
01:55:52.823 --> 01:55:54.366
Dangerous.

1510
01:55:54.575 --> 01:55:58.078
You've turned every cell phone
in Gotham into a microphone.

1511
01:55:58.245 --> 01:56:00.664
And a high-frequency generator-receiver.

1512
01:56:00.831 --> 01:56:05.919
You took my sonar concept
and applied it to every phone in the city.

1513
01:56:06.086 --> 01:56:10.674
With half the city feeding you sonar.
you can image all of Gotham.

1514
01:56:12.593 --> 01:56:13.969
This is wrong.

1515
01:56:14.136 --> 01:56:16.180
I've gotta find this man. Lucius.

1516
01:56:18.182 --> 01:56:19.474
At what cost?

1517
01:56:19.641 --> 01:56:22.436
The database is null-key encrypted.

1518
01:56:22.603 --> 01:56:24.813
It can only be accessed by one person.

1519
01:56:26.148 --> 01:56:28.317
This is too much power for one person.

1520
01:56:28.484 --> 01:56:30.652
That's why I gave it to you.

1521
01:56:31.111 --> 01:56:32.321
Only you can use it.

1522
01:56:32.488 --> 01:56:36.283
Spying on 30 million people
isn't part of my job description.

1523
01:56:38.494 --> 01:56:42.206
This is an audio sample. If he talks
within range of any phone in the city...

1524
01:56:42.372 --> 01:56:44.583
...you can triangulate his position.

1525
01:56:45.042 --> 01:56:47.544
I'll help you this one time.

1526
01:56:48.003 --> 01:56:49.796
But consider this my resignation.

1527
01:56:49.963 --> 01:56:54.551
As long as this machine is
at Wayne Enterprises. I won't be.

1528
01:56:55.302 --> 01:56:57.221
When you're finished...

1529
01:56:57.888 --> 01:56:59.014
...type in your name.

1530
01:57:07.606 --> 01:57:10.692
My officers are going over
every inch of the tunnels and bridges...

1531
01:57:10.859 --> 01:57:14.071
...but with the Joker's threat.
they're not an option.

1532
01:57:14.238 --> 01:57:17.074
- And land routes east?
- Backed up for hours.

1533
01:57:17.241 --> 01:57:20.869
Which leaves the ferries
with 30.000 ready to board.

1534
01:57:21.036 --> 01:57:24.081
I wanna use the ferries so I can
get those prisoners off the island.

1535
01:57:24.414 --> 01:57:27.209
The men you put away?
Those aren't people I'm worried about.

1536
01:57:27.376 --> 01:57:29.503
You should be.
Whatever the Joker's planning...

1537
01:57:29.670 --> 01:57:34.174
...it's a good bet Harvey's prisoners are
involved. I wanna get them out of here.

1538
01:57:35.634 --> 01:57:36.844
So where is Harvey?

1539
01:57:37.427 --> 01:57:40.597
- We haven't found him.
- Oh. Jesus.

1540
01:57:44.434 --> 01:57:46.520
How long can you keep this quiet?

1541
01:58:00.617 --> 01:58:03.287
Don't stop for lights. cops. nothing.

1542
01:58:04.121 --> 01:58:06.290
Going to join your wife?

1543
01:58:09.793 --> 01:58:12.296
- You love her?
- Yes.

1544
01:58:13.172 --> 01:58:16.133
You ever imagine what it would be like
to listen to her die?

1545
01:58:16.300 --> 01:58:17.801
Look. take it up with the Joker.

1546
01:58:17.968 --> 01:58:21.221
He killed your woman. He made you...

1547
01:58:21.388 --> 01:58:22.431
...like this.

1548
01:58:22.806 --> 01:58:25.809
The Joker's just a mad dog.

1549
01:58:25.976 --> 01:58:28.604
I want whoever let him off the leash.

1550
01:58:29.313 --> 01:58:32.649
I took care of Wuertz. but who was
your other man inside Gordon's unit?

1551
01:58:32.816 --> 01:58:35.444
Who picked up Rachel?
Must have been someone she trusted.

1552
01:58:36.653 --> 01:58:38.780
Look. if I tell you...

1553
01:58:38.947 --> 01:58:39.990
...will you let me go?

1554
01:58:40.741 --> 01:58:42.075
Can't hurt your chances.

1555
01:58:44.828 --> 01:58:46.497
It was Ramirez.

1556
01:58:51.919 --> 01:58:55.172
- But you said...
- I said it couldn't hurt your chances.

1557
01:58:58.759 --> 01:59:00.886
You're a lucky man.

1558
01:59:04.348 --> 01:59:06.099
- But he's not.
- Who?

1559
01:59:09.019 --> 01:59:10.437
Your driver.

1560
01:59:23.659 --> 01:59:24.701
Stand back.

1561
01:59:24.868 --> 01:59:27.204
Hey. that ain't right.
We should be on that boat.

1562
01:59:27.371 --> 01:59:29.957
You wanna ride across
with them? Be my guest.

1563
01:59:49.059 --> 01:59:51.061
ENGINES STOP

1564
01:59:53.188 --> 01:59:54.898
Sir. they've stopped their engines.

1565
01:59:55.065 --> 01:59:56.108
Right. get on the radio.

1566
01:59:56.275 --> 01:59:59.903
Tell them we'll come back and pick
them up once we dump the scumbags.

1567
02:00:00.070 --> 02:00:02.447
Liberty. this is Spirit. Come in.

1568
02:00:04.491 --> 02:00:05.701
What the heck was that?

1569
02:00:07.619 --> 02:00:09.079
What the...?

1570
02:00:09.621 --> 02:00:12.916
Liberty.
come in. please. This is Spirit. Come in.

1571
02:00:14.543 --> 02:00:16.420
Liberty. we have the same thing.
We've lost both engines.

1572
02:00:16.587 --> 02:00:18.088
- Liberty. come in.
Fox.

1573
02:00:18.255 --> 02:00:20.757
There's something going on
on the ferries.

1574
02:00:21.508 --> 02:00:23.802
Get down to the engine room now.

1575
02:00:24.428 --> 02:00:26.638
Hey. buddy. what's happening?

1576
02:00:35.230 --> 02:00:38.692
Captain. we got a hundred barrels
down there rigged to blow. And this.

1577
02:00:51.788 --> 02:00:52.873
Oh. my God.

1578
02:00:53.040 --> 02:00:54.875
Looks like some kind of detonator.

1579
02:00:55.042 --> 02:00:57.920
Why would they give us
the detonator to our own bomb?

1580
02:01:00.839 --> 02:01:02.216
Tonight. you're all gonna...

1581
02:01:02.382 --> 02:01:04.134
...be a part of a social experiment.

1582
02:01:07.971 --> 02:01:11.809
Through the magic of diesel fuel
and ammonium nitrate...

1583
02:01:11.975 --> 02:01:16.063
...I'm ready right now
to blow you all sky-high.

1584
02:01:16.230 --> 02:01:18.315
Liberty. come in. over.

1585
02:01:19.775 --> 02:01:20.818
It's dead.

1586
02:01:21.151 --> 02:01:25.656
If anyone attempts
to get off their boat. you all die.

1587
02:01:25.989 --> 02:01:27.282
I'm zeroing in.

1588
02:01:27.449 --> 02:01:31.995
Each of you has a remote
to blow up the other boat.

1589
02:01:32.162 --> 02:01:34.623
His voice is on the ferry...

1590
02:01:34.790 --> 02:01:36.834
...but it's not the source.

1591
02:01:39.086 --> 02:01:40.212
West.

1592
02:01:47.469 --> 02:01:49.763
- Gordon.
I have the Joker's location.

1593
02:01:49.930 --> 02:01:51.014
Prewitt Building.

1594
02:01:51.181 --> 02:01:53.642
Assemble on the building opposite.

1595
02:01:55.018 --> 02:01:57.813
At midnight. I blow you all up.

1596
02:01:57.980 --> 02:02:03.152
If. however. one of you presses
the button. I'll let that boat live.

1597
02:02:03.318 --> 02:02:05.445
So who 's it gonna be?

1598
02:02:05.612 --> 02:02:08.157
Harvey Dent's most-wanted
scumbag collection...

1599
02:02:08.323 --> 02:02:11.660
...or the sweet and innocent civilians?

1600
02:02:11.827 --> 02:02:14.371
You choose.

1601
02:02:14.538 --> 02:02:16.456
Oh. and you might wanna
decide quickly...

1602
02:02:16.623 --> 02:02:20.961
...because the people on the other boat
may not be quite so noble.

1603
02:02:28.343 --> 02:02:29.386
Stay back.

1604
02:02:29.553 --> 02:02:33.348
Well. now. who are you to decide?
We ought to talk this over. at least.

1605
02:02:33.724 --> 02:02:37.311
We don't all have to die.
Those men had their chance.

1606
02:02:37.936 --> 02:02:41.732
- We are not going to talk about this.
- Why aren't we talking about it?

1607
02:02:41.899 --> 02:02:44.485
They're talking over the same thing
on the other boat.

1608
02:02:44.651 --> 02:02:46.945
- Let's put it to a vote.
Yes!

1609
02:02:52.242 --> 02:02:54.828
- Hello?
Barbara. it's Anna Ramirez.

1610
02:02:54.995 --> 02:02:58.040
Jim needs you to pack up
and put the kids in the car right away.

1611
02:02:58.207 --> 02:02:59.917
But the units outside...

1612
02:03:00.083 --> 02:03:01.668
Those cops can 't be trusted.

1613
02:03:01.835 --> 02:03:04.796
Jim needs you away from them
as soon as possible.

1614
02:03:04.963 --> 02:03:07.925
I'll call them off for 10 minutes.
and you'll have to move fast.

1615
02:03:08.091 --> 02:03:11.929
- But where am I supposed to take them?
- 250 52nd Street.

1616
02:03:12.095 --> 02:03:13.972
Leave as soon as
the patrol car pulls out.

1617
02:03:14.139 --> 02:03:15.516
Okay.

1618
02:03:15.891 --> 02:03:17.684
She believe you?

1619
02:03:17.893 --> 02:03:19.937
It's because she trusts you...

1620
02:03:20.270 --> 02:03:21.355
...just like Rachel did.

1621
02:03:21.522 --> 02:03:23.607
- I didn't know...
- Didn't know what they'd do?

1622
02:03:23.774 --> 02:03:26.527
You're the second cop to say that to me.

1623
02:03:26.777 --> 02:03:28.904
What exactly did you think
they were gonna do?

1624
02:03:29.071 --> 02:03:31.323
They got me early on.
My mother's hospital bills...

1625
02:03:31.490 --> 02:03:34.535
- Don't!
- I'm sorry.

1626
02:03:35.077 --> 02:03:37.538
You live to fight another day. officer.

1627
02:03:41.333 --> 02:03:43.168
We found the missing hospital bus.

1628
02:03:43.335 --> 02:03:45.045
Then we have a hostage situation.

1629
02:03:47.130 --> 02:03:49.132
It's a shooting gallery.

1630
02:03:49.508 --> 02:03:51.802
Why would he choose a spot
with such big windows?

1631
02:03:51.969 --> 02:03:53.804
We have clear shots on five clowns.

1632
02:03:53.971 --> 02:03:56.723
Snipers take them out.
smash the windows. a team rappels in.

1633
02:03:57.141 --> 02:03:58.642
Team moves in by the stairwells.

1634
02:03:58.809 --> 02:04:00.936
Two. three casualties max.

1635
02:04:01.103 --> 02:04:02.980
- Let's do it.
It's not that simple.

1636
02:04:03.147 --> 02:04:05.482
- With the Joker. it never is.
- What's simple is...

1637
02:04:05.649 --> 02:04:08.819
...every second. those people on
the ferries get closer to blowing...

1638
02:04:08.986 --> 02:04:11.530
- That won't happen.
- Then he'll blow both of them up!

1639
02:04:11.697 --> 02:04:15.450
- We don't have time for paper ballots.
- I want everybody to put their votes...

1640
02:04:15.617 --> 02:04:17.619
...on this piece of paper.

1641
02:04:18.662 --> 02:04:21.498
If anyone's got pens. pass it along.

1642
02:04:21.832 --> 02:04:23.625
Thank you.
Anybody else?

1643
02:04:23.792 --> 02:04:25.627
Coming through. Anybody else?
Thank you.

1644
02:04:25.794 --> 02:04:28.672
We need to get these votes in quickly.

1645
02:04:28.839 --> 02:04:30.382
Come on.

1646
02:04:32.384 --> 02:04:34.511
What are you waiting for?
Push the button!

1647
02:04:34.678 --> 02:04:36.638
We're running out of time!

1648
02:04:37.931 --> 02:04:39.766
I need five minutes alone.

1649
02:04:39.933 --> 02:04:41.768
No! There's no time!

1650
02:04:41.935 --> 02:04:43.353
We have clear shots!

1651
02:04:43.520 --> 02:04:46.440
Dent is in there with them.
We have to save Dent!

1652
02:04:46.607 --> 02:04:48.567
I have to save Dent.

1653
02:04:48.734 --> 02:04:49.860
Get ready.

1654
02:04:52.696 --> 02:04:55.365
Two minutes. then we breach.

1655
02:05:00.954 --> 02:05:02.456
Fox. I need picture.

1656
02:05:05.501 --> 02:05:07.961
- Hello?
Jim. we're in trouble.

1657
02:05:09.213 --> 02:05:11.507
Okay. you got POV on alpha...

1658
02:05:12.549 --> 02:05:14.510
...omni on beta.

1659
02:05:15.969 --> 02:05:19.348
Looks like clowns and hostages
on two floors.

1660
02:05:19.515 --> 02:05:21.934
There's a SWA T team on the stairwell.

1661
02:05:25.229 --> 02:05:27.856
Another SWA T team on the roof.

1662
02:05:29.399 --> 02:05:30.609
Line's clear.

1663
02:05:32.361 --> 02:05:35.072
- Barbara. calm down.
- He has the kids!

1664
02:05:35.239 --> 02:05:38.492
Hello. Jim.
- Harvey?

1665
02:05:39.284 --> 02:05:42.496
- Where's my family?
- Where my family died.

1666
02:05:45.582 --> 02:05:47.251
Blue team. acquire the target.

1667
02:05:48.919 --> 02:05:51.505
Entry team. set your charge.

1668
02:06:07.437 --> 02:06:09.273
Fox. the SWA Ts are
targeting the wrong people.

1669
02:06:09.439 --> 02:06:10.941
The clowns are the hostages.

1670
02:06:11.650 --> 02:06:13.443
Red team. go! Red team. go!

1671
02:06:17.197 --> 02:06:18.615
Entry team. blow and go!

1672
02:06:22.703 --> 02:06:24.121
Don't move.

1673
02:06:25.289 --> 02:06:26.665
Take the shot.

1674
02:06:32.296 --> 02:06:33.964
Those SWATs are coming in hot.

1675
02:06:34.131 --> 02:06:35.966
Clowns. put down your guns.

1676
02:06:36.466 --> 02:06:39.094
Drop your weapons!
On the ground. now!

1677
02:06:39.303 --> 02:06:42.473
Doctors. get down!
Clear the line of fire. Drop your weap...

1678
02:07:07.080 --> 02:07:08.248
Freeze!

1679
02:07:08.415 --> 02:07:10.792
Stand down or you will be...

1680
02:07:14.338 --> 02:07:15.797
Look up.

1681
02:07:16.381 --> 02:07:18.967
See those bad guys on the floor above?

1682
02:07:19.134 --> 02:07:22.137
They're waiting to ambush
the SWAT team coming up the elevator.

1683
02:07:22.596 --> 02:07:23.639
Sixty seconds.

1684
02:07:31.939 --> 02:07:36.527
The tally is 140 against. 396 for.

1685
02:07:44.660 --> 02:07:47.204
So go ahead. Do it.

1686
02:07:47.371 --> 02:07:49.373
We're still here.

1687
02:07:50.541 --> 02:07:53.502
And that means they haven't
killed us yet either.

1688
02:07:54.962 --> 02:07:56.713
Go. go. go!

1689
02:07:56.880 --> 02:07:58.674
Blue team. cover!

1690
02:08:04.179 --> 02:08:05.848
Trouble on the floor above.

1691
02:08:15.190 --> 02:08:16.567
Get down on the ground now!

1692
02:08:24.992 --> 02:08:27.411
Freeze! Stop or we will shoot.

1693
02:08:27.578 --> 02:08:29.580
We will shoot you. Drop the officer.

1694
02:08:29.746 --> 02:08:31.290
Release the officer right now.

1695
02:08:31.456 --> 02:08:33.417
Let him go now!
On your knees!

1696
02:08:34.001 --> 02:08:36.086
We got him. He's out of the game.

1697
02:08:36.253 --> 02:08:38.755
Keep your hands in the air!
Step away from the edge!

1698
02:08:46.805 --> 02:08:48.432
Halt!

1699
02:09:01.737 --> 02:09:03.113
Stay down!
Don't move!

1700
02:09:03.280 --> 02:09:07.576
Be advised. Clowns
are hostages. doctors are targets.

1701
02:09:13.874 --> 02:09:16.043
Ah. you made it. I'm so thrilled.

1702
02:09:16.210 --> 02:09:19.379
- Where's the detonator?
- Go get him.

1703
02:09:32.768 --> 02:09:35.854
Put down your weapon!
Don't move!

1704
02:10:07.261 --> 02:10:09.138
You don't wanna die...

1705
02:10:09.304 --> 02:10:12.349
...but you don't know how to take a life.

1706
02:10:12.516 --> 02:10:14.184
Give it to me.

1707
02:10:14.476 --> 02:10:18.814
These men will kill you
and take it anyway.

1708
02:10:22.234 --> 02:10:24.736
No one wants to get their hands dirty.

1709
02:10:24.903 --> 02:10:27.865
Fine. I'll do it.

1710
02:10:29.533 --> 02:10:32.244
Those men on that boat?
They made their choices.

1711
02:10:32.411 --> 02:10:34.705
They chose to murder and steal.

1712
02:10:34.872 --> 02:10:38.083
It doesn't make any sense
for us to have to die too.

1713
02:10:47.551 --> 02:10:50.012
All the old familiar places.

1714
02:10:56.310 --> 02:10:57.394
Stand by.

1715
02:11:07.738 --> 02:11:11.325
Red team. floor secure.
Hostages are safe.

1716
02:11:11.533 --> 02:11:13.619
Give it to me.

1717
02:11:15.037 --> 02:11:18.790
You can tell them I took it by force.

1718
02:11:19.291 --> 02:11:24.213
Give it to me. and I'll do what
you should've did 10 minutes ago.

1719
02:11:46.276 --> 02:11:49.613
We really should stop this fighting.
otherwise we'll miss the fireworks.

1720
02:11:49.780 --> 02:11:51.615
There won't be any fireworks.

1721
02:11:52.032 --> 02:11:55.244
And here we go.

1722
02:12:34.575 --> 02:12:36.493
What were you trying to prove?

1723
02:12:36.660 --> 02:12:39.621
That deep down.
everyone's as ugly as you?

1724
02:12:40.747 --> 02:12:41.790
You're alone.

1725
02:12:48.380 --> 02:12:53.886
Can't rely on anyone these days. You
gotta do everything yourself. Don't we?

1726
02:12:54.094 --> 02:12:56.930
That's okay. I came prepared.

1727
02:12:57.139 --> 02:13:01.602
It's a funny world we live in. Speaking of
which. you know how I got these scars?

1728
02:13:01.768 --> 02:13:04.605
No. but I know how you got these.

1729
02:13:22.414 --> 02:13:25.167
Oh. you.

1730
02:13:25.334 --> 02:13:28.378
You just couldn't let me go. could you?

1731
02:13:29.505 --> 02:13:33.425
This is what happens
when an unstoppable force...

1732
02:13:33.592 --> 02:13:38.055
...meets an immovable object.

1733
02:13:38.639 --> 02:13:44.061
You truly are incorruptible. aren't you?

1734
02:13:44.228 --> 02:13:46.939
Huh? You won't kill me...

1735
02:13:47.105 --> 02:13:53.362
...out of some misplaced sense
of self-righteousness.

1736
02:13:53.529 --> 02:13:56.740
And I won't kill you...

1737
02:13:56.907 --> 02:14:00.702
...because you're just too much fun.

1738
02:14:01.745 --> 02:14:05.916
I think you and I are destined
to do this forever.

1739
02:14:06.083 --> 02:14:08.085
You'll be in a padded cell forever.

1740
02:14:08.252 --> 02:14:10.087
Maybe we could share one.

1741
02:14:10.254 --> 02:14:11.713
You know.
they'll be doubling up...

1742
02:14:11.880 --> 02:14:14.424
...the rate this city's inhabitants
are losing their minds.

1743
02:14:14.591 --> 02:14:17.719
This city just showed you...

1744
02:14:17.886 --> 02:14:21.932
...that it's full of people
ready to believe in good.

1745
02:14:22.099 --> 02:14:25.269
Until their spirit breaks completely.

1746
02:14:26.145 --> 02:14:30.983
Until they get a good look
at the real Harvey Dent...

1747
02:14:31.150 --> 02:14:33.944
...and all the heroic things he's done.

1748
02:14:35.612 --> 02:14:40.659
You didn't think I'd risk losing the battle
for Gotham's soul...

1749
02:14:40.826 --> 02:14:43.745
...in a fistfight with you?

1750
02:14:44.288 --> 02:14:45.831
No.

1751
02:14:45.998 --> 02:14:49.418
You need an ace in the hole.

1752
02:14:49.585 --> 02:14:51.211
Mine's Harvey.

1753
02:14:51.587 --> 02:14:53.297
What did you do?

1754
02:14:53.463 --> 02:14:56.466
I took Gotham's white knight...

1755
02:14:56.633 --> 02:15:00.262
...and I brought him down to our level.

1756
02:15:00.679 --> 02:15:03.640
It wasn't hard.
See. madness. as you know...

1757
02:15:03.807 --> 02:15:06.852
...is like gravity.

1758
02:15:07.019 --> 02:15:09.354
All it takes is a little push.

1759
02:15:26.288 --> 02:15:28.040
Dent!

1760
02:15:49.019 --> 02:15:53.357
This is where they brought her.
Gordon. after your men handed her over.

1761
02:15:54.107 --> 02:15:55.692
This is where she died.

1762
02:15:55.859 --> 02:15:58.195
I know. I was here...

1763
02:15:59.238 --> 02:16:01.990
...trying to save her.
- But you didn't.

1764
02:16:02.282 --> 02:16:04.034
- I couldn't.
- Yes. you could've.

1765
02:16:04.201 --> 02:16:05.702
If you'd listened to me.

1766
02:16:05.869 --> 02:16:08.497
If you stood up against corruption...

1767
02:16:08.664 --> 02:16:10.874
...instead of doing your deal
with the devil.

1768
02:16:11.041 --> 02:16:12.668
I was trying to fight the Mob!

1769
02:16:13.168 --> 02:16:18.006
You wouldn't dare try to justify yourself
if you knew what I'd lost.

1770
02:16:19.299 --> 02:16:22.427
Have you ever had to talk to the person
you loved most...

1771
02:16:22.594 --> 02:16:26.473
...tell them it's gonna be all right.
when you know it's not?

1772
02:16:28.142 --> 02:16:32.020
Well. you're about to know
what that feels like. Gordon.

1773
02:16:32.771 --> 02:16:36.650
Then you can look me in the eye
and tell me you're sorry.

1774
02:16:38.402 --> 02:16:41.989
- You're not going to hurt my family.
- No.

1775
02:16:42.156 --> 02:16:44.867
Just the person you love most.

1776
02:16:52.875 --> 02:16:55.919
So is it your wife?

1777
02:16:57.004 --> 02:16:58.672
Put the gun down. Harvey.

1778
02:16:59.047 --> 02:17:00.716
Harvey. put down the gun.

1779
02:17:00.883 --> 02:17:04.428
Please. Please. Harvey. Please.

1780
02:17:05.804 --> 02:17:07.097
Oh. goddamn it.

1781
02:17:07.264 --> 02:17:09.433
Will you stop pointing that gun
at my family?

1782
02:17:09.933 --> 02:17:11.602
No!
- We have a winner.

1783
02:17:11.768 --> 02:17:13.270
No. Jim. stop him!

1784
02:17:13.770 --> 02:17:15.606
Harvey.
Don't let him...

1785
02:17:15.772 --> 02:17:16.899
Harvey!

1786
02:17:18.275 --> 02:17:20.152
I'm sorry!

1787
02:17:21.945 --> 02:17:23.030
For everything.

1788
02:17:25.616 --> 02:17:27.826
Please don't hurt my son.

1789
02:17:37.961 --> 02:17:39.546
You brought your cops?

1790
02:17:39.713 --> 02:17:42.591
All they know is there's a situation.

1791
02:17:42.758 --> 02:17:45.761
They don't know who or what.
They're just creating a perimeter.

1792
02:17:45.928 --> 02:17:48.597
You think I wanna escape from this?

1793
02:17:48.764 --> 02:17:51.517
There is no escape from this.

1794
02:17:51.683 --> 02:17:53.811
You don't wanna hurt the boy. Harvey.

1795
02:17:56.104 --> 02:17:59.316
It's not about what I want.
it's about what's fair!

1796
02:18:00.067 --> 02:18:04.279
You thought we could be decent men
in an indecent time.

1797
02:18:07.074 --> 02:18:08.158
But you were wrong.

1798
02:18:08.867 --> 02:18:12.663
The world is cruel. And the only morality
in a cruel world...

1799
02:18:13.413 --> 02:18:15.332
...is chance.

1800
02:18:15.499 --> 02:18:17.209
Unbiased.

1801
02:18:17.417 --> 02:18:18.669
Unprejudiced.

1802
02:18:20.045 --> 02:18:21.171
Fair.

1803
02:18:21.338 --> 02:18:23.590
His son's got the same chance she had.

1804
02:18:24.341 --> 02:18:25.634
Fifty-fifty.

1805
02:18:25.801 --> 02:18:29.263
What happened to Rachel wasn't
chance. We decided to act.

1806
02:18:29.596 --> 02:18:30.931
We three.

1807
02:18:31.098 --> 02:18:34.518
Then why was it me who was
the only one who lost everything?

1808
02:18:37.020 --> 02:18:39.648
- It wasn't.
- The Joker chose me.

1809
02:18:39.815 --> 02:18:42.109
Because you were the best of us.

1810
02:18:42.276 --> 02:18:47.281
He wanted to prove that
even someone as good as you...

1811
02:18:47.447 --> 02:18:49.199
...could fall.

1812
02:18:49.533 --> 02:18:50.826
And he was right.

1813
02:18:50.993 --> 02:18:53.245
You're the one pointing the gun. Harvey.

1814
02:18:53.412 --> 02:18:56.456
So point it at the people responsible.

1815
02:18:57.416 --> 02:18:59.251
Fair enough.

1816
02:19:02.588 --> 02:19:04.464
You first.

1817
02:19:16.977 --> 02:19:18.645
My turn.

1818
02:19:25.569 --> 02:19:27.571
Harvey. you're right.

1819
02:19:28.614 --> 02:19:31.241
Rachel's death was my fault.

1820
02:19:34.328 --> 02:19:36.788
Please don't punish the boy.

1821
02:19:37.873 --> 02:19:41.084
- Please. punish me.
- I'm about to.

1822
02:19:43.045 --> 02:19:45.005
Tell your boy
he's gonna be all right. Gordon.

1823
02:19:45.464 --> 02:19:47.090
Lie...

1824
02:19:47.591 --> 02:19:48.717
...like I lied.

1825
02:19:52.471 --> 02:19:54.056
It's going to be all right. son.

1826
02:20:32.469 --> 02:20:35.305
Dad? Daddy. is he okay?

1827
02:20:51.822 --> 02:20:53.991
- Thank you.
- You don't have to thank me.

1828
02:20:54.616 --> 02:20:56.410
Yes. I do.

1829
02:21:00.664 --> 02:21:01.999
The Joker won.

1830
02:21:04.418 --> 02:21:07.296
Harvey's prosecution.
everything he fought for...

1831
02:21:07.838 --> 02:21:09.590
...undone.

1832
02:21:10.090 --> 02:21:15.012
Whatever chance you gave us at fixing
our city dies with Harvey's reputation.

1833
02:21:15.179 --> 02:21:16.346
We bet it all on him.

1834
02:21:17.681 --> 02:21:20.559
The Joker took the best of us
and tore him down.

1835
02:21:21.143 --> 02:21:22.561
People will lose hope.

1836
02:21:22.728 --> 02:21:24.480
They won't.

1837
02:21:26.982 --> 02:21:28.859
They must never know what he did.

1838
02:21:29.026 --> 02:21:30.861
Five dead.

1839
02:21:31.153 --> 02:21:32.446
Two of them cops.

1840
02:21:32.613 --> 02:21:35.073
- You can't sweep that...
- No.

1841
02:21:39.870 --> 02:21:42.706
But the Joker cannot win.

1842
02:21:47.961 --> 02:21:51.173
Gotham needs its true hero.

1843
02:21:57.554 --> 02:22:00.599
- No.
- You either die a hero...

1844
02:22:00.766 --> 02:22:05.229
...or you live long enough
to see yourself become the villain.

1845
02:22:05.395 --> 02:22:07.231
I can do those things...

1846
02:22:07.648 --> 02:22:10.692
...because I'm not a hero. not like Dent.

1847
02:22:13.695 --> 02:22:16.573
I killed those people.
That's what I can be.

1848
02:22:16.740 --> 02:22:18.659
No. no. you can't. You're not.

1849
02:22:18.826 --> 02:22:21.411
I'm whatever Gotham needs me to be.

1850
02:22:23.080 --> 02:22:24.206
Call it in.

1851
02:22:27.501 --> 02:22:29.253
A hero.

1852
02:22:29.419 --> 02:22:32.673
Not the hero we deserved.
but the hero we needed.

1853
02:22:33.257 --> 02:22:35.801
Nothing less than a knight...

1854
02:22:36.343 --> 02:22:38.053
...shining.

1855
02:22:38.679 --> 02:22:40.305
They'll hunt you.

1856
02:22:40.472 --> 02:22:42.266
You'll hunt me.

1857
02:22:42.766 --> 02:22:44.726
You'll condemn me.

1858
02:22:45.435 --> 02:22:47.729
Set the dogs on me.

1859
02:22:51.483 --> 02:22:53.777
Because that's what needs to happen.

1860
02:22:54.945 --> 02:22:56.864
Because sometimes...

1861
02:22:57.030 --> 02:22:59.199
...the truth isn 't good enough.

1862
02:23:00.075 --> 02:23:02.369
Sometimes people deserve more.

1863
02:23:05.831 --> 02:23:09.751
Sometimes people deserve
to have their faith rewarded.

1864
02:23:28.145 --> 02:23:29.813
Batman.

1865
02:23:31.732 --> 02:23:33.484
Batman!

1866
02:23:34.276 --> 02:23:36.236
Why's he running. Dad?

1867
02:23:37.279 --> 02:23:38.614
Because we have to chase him.

1868
02:23:38.780 --> 02:23:41.658
Okay. we're going in! Go. go! Move!

1869
02:23:47.748 --> 02:23:49.333
He didn't do anything wrong.

1870
02:23:52.085 --> 02:23:57.674
Because he's the hero Gotham deserves.
but not the one it needs right now.

1871
02:23:59.092 --> 02:24:00.135
So we'll hunt him...

1872
02:24:03.263 --> 02:24:05.349
...because he can take it.

1873
02:24:07.851 --> 02:24:10.354
Because he's not our hero.

1874
02:24:17.903 --> 02:24:19.112
He's a silent guardian...

1875
02:24:20.280 --> 02:24:22.157
...a watchful protector.

1876
02:24:24.660 --> 02:24:25.953
A dark knight.

1877
02:24:26.305 --> 02:25:26.688
